title: poppy seed filling
directions: Put
butter
in
deep
skillet and melt.
Add flour and cook a little (do not brown), add water. Then add ground poppy seed, salt
and
sugar.
Cook over low heat until the mixture thickens and is
soft
to taste, about 30 minutes or so, stirring occasionally so as not to stick to pan.
This mixture may be kept in refrigerator and used as needed for kolaches, poppy seed roll or just eating as dessert.

title: favorite fudge brownies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and cocoa.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add vanilla, salt, baking powder and flour and mix together.
Add pecans.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Double if you want a 9 x 13 x 2-inch.

title: sandy's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a Bundt pan (greased and floured) for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar plum bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice and salt in large bowl; set aside.
Combine eggs, oil and baby food in a separate bowl.
Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients; mix just until moistened.
Fold in pecans.
Divide batter evenly between 2 ungreased loaf pans.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in loaf comes out clean.
Cool in pan. Makes 2 loaves.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop vegetables and add cheese, chips and dressing.
Brown hamburger.
Add salt and kidney beans and simmer 10 minutes.
Add to lettuce mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook over hot water until tender (45 minutes) rice in 2 cups milk and salt.
Last 1/2 hour stir in raisins.
Next stir in remaining 2 cups milk, beaten egg yolks, cinnamon and vanilla. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Next, carefully fold in 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into casserole and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: petits fours
directions: Cream together the butter and shortening.
Add 1 cup sugar and cream until light.
Add the extracts.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to batter.
Beat egg whites until foamy and add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat to soft peak. Fold into batter.
Turn into greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool.
Cut into shapes.

title: cornbread
directions: Whisk first 4 ingredients; stir in corn and sour cream.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: white fudge
directions: Lightly butter an 8 inch square dish and set aside.
In a heavy sauce pan combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and the mixture reaches a boil.
Boil 9 to 10 minutes until 238° on a candy thermometer, or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and let stand until cooled and 110°.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Quickly stir in pecans and cherries.
Pour into buttered dish and let stand until firm. Makes 1 1/2 lbs.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix together everything except 7-Up until well blended, then add 7-Up.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, the first 10 minutes at 350°, then turn down to 300°.
Do not preheat oven.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in an unbaked pie shell. Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven until firm and slightly brown.

title: peach glow angel cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box for 10-inch tube pan. Cool and remove from pan. Slice a 1-inch layer from the top of the cake. Scoop out center to within 1-inch of side and bottom. Prepare pudding mix with milk using package directions. Mix half the pudding with pie filling in bowl. Spoon the pudding/pie filling mixture into the cavity of the cake. Replace the top layer. Chill until filling is firm. Fold remaining pudding into whipped cream to make frosting for top and sides of cake. Chill until serving time.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with crumbs.
Save some for on top. Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix jello with boiling water; chill.
Add milk and whip until peaks form. Combine with cream cheese mixture.
Pour into pretzel crust.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Bring water to a full, rolling boil.
Add grits and return to boiling point.
Cook, stirring constantly, until very thick, about 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter or margarine and mix cheese, eggs and pepper.
Stir into grits.
Pour into baking dish and bake 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: easy jam cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box, except leave out 1/2 cup of the water it calls for and add the jam.
Cook as usual.

title: aunty theresa's "raisin squares"
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Let simmer slowly.
When done, add lump of butter or margarine.
When slightly cool, add lemon juice and a little grated rind.
When cool, bake between pie crusts. Top crust with a little cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and you'll wish you had doubled the recipe!!

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Shape into balls and arrange in saucepan or deep skillet.
Combine soup, water and a little tomato paste.
Mix and pour over meat balls.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes, macaroni or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: chicken broccoli supreme
directions: Put cooked broccoli in bottom of pan; next layer chicken, then combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon and curry to make a sauce.
Place sauce over chicken; cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
After baking, add rings and brown under broiler.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli; cut florets off and dry on paper towel. Microwave or fry bacon until crisp.
Place on paper plate lined with paper towel.
Wipe off excess grease.
Cool and crumble.
Chop medium onion; place florets, bacon, onion and cheese in a bowl. Mix together.
Refrigerate while mixing dressing.
In a quart bowl, add mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix with fork or whisk.
Add to salad 1/2 hour before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: noodles and cheese
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add noodles and cottage cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat mixture and serve.

title: layered salad
directions: Arrange the following by layers in a bowl. A large glass salad bowl is very effective.

title: orange julius
directions: Whip all ingredients in blender.
Gradually add ice.

title: cajun seafood bisque
directions: Add all ingredients and dilute with milk to desired consistency.
I like to use an imitation seafood mix (crab and lobster chunks, fresh shrimp, clams).
Heat over a medium heat until hot.
Put into warmed crock-pot and serve from the crock-pot for gatherings.

title: chili cheese strata
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole, arrange bread cubes evenly. Sprinkle 1-cup cheese evenly over cubes.
Pour chili salsa to cover evenly; set aside.
In large bowl, mix together next 5 ingredients; pour over bread.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover; refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Uncover, dust top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: irish whiskey pie
directions: In
small mixing bowl, combine dessert mix and coffee powder. Add milk and beat at high speed for 1 minute; blend in water and whiskey.
Beat at high speed 2 more minutes until fluffy. Carefully fold in the whipped filling.
Pour into pastry shell and chill 3-4 hours.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and celery in fat.
Add hamburger; cook until done. Add seasonings.
Add tomato sauce, water, tomatoes, green chilies and beans.
Simmer 2 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown first four ingredients in large soup pot, drain fat.
Add taco seasoning.
Add ingredients.
Heat and serve hot with Cheddar cheese and crushed corn chips.
Freezes well.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and margarine together; press into a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Beat together cream cheese, eggs, 2 teaspoons vanilla and lemon juice for 10 minutes.
Mix in 1 cup sugar and beat 3 to 4 minutes more.
Pour batter over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken or turkey salad
directions: Mix.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, blend cake mix, sour cream, oil, 1/4 cup sugar, water and eggs.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter in 10-inch or fluted pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 375° or until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream the butter, which should have softened at room temperature, with the sugar until the granules of sugar have disappeared.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in the cornmeal and add the lemon juice and grated rind.
(You should have at least 1/3 cup of lemon juice as the pie should taste lemony.)
Pour into an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 375° until the pie is firm.
Oldtimers shook the pie slightly and if the center trembled a little, a few more minutes were needed.

title: city chicken
directions: Cut round steak in strips.
Wrap steak around onion, then wrap bacon around steak.
Pierce with toothpick.
Brown in skillet. Add 3 cups water and 3 bouillon cubes.
Simmer until tender.
Add package of egg noodles to broth; cook until tender.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Put mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: fannie casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper until tender.
When meat is brown add tomatoes and peas.
Remove from heat.
Drain some liquid off and add mushroom soup.
Set aside.

title: ritz bits mix
directions: In a large pan, mix together Ritz Bits and nuts.
Set aside. In a saucepan, mix together sugar, butter and Karo.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over Ritz Bits and nuts.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour out on wax paper.
Cool and serve.

title: raisin bars
directions: Cook raisins in water for 5 minutes.
Take 1 cup of raisin liquid and add butter or oleo and let cool.
Mix flour, cinnamon, salt, sugar, baking powder, soda and nuts.
Add liquid mixture and drained raisins.

title: butterballs
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together; work in butter and vanilla.
Add nuts; mix well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for about 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll cookies in powdered sugar while warm.
Expensive, but delicious and keeps well.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and cream over boiling water.
Add pecans.
Drop on greased wax paper.
Put in refrigerator until cold.
Melt together Hershey bar, chocolate chips and wax.
Dip caramel into this mixture.
Be sure and grease the wax paper.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: To softened cheese add diced beef and onions. Save 1/2 c.
of the beef.
Mix cheese, Accent, beef and onions by hand.
Form into ball and roll in rest of beef.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: great pumpkin spice cake
directions: Dissolve soda in water.
Combine ingredients and pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tests done.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 muffin tins.
Mash bananas, stir in sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with oil.
Stir in nuts and peaches.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake 25-30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Brown onions, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Add diced and crushed tomatoes.
Add all other ingredients.
Add salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook and stir onion and green pepper in oil in 10-inch skillet until onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in rice, water chestnuts, mushrooms and soy sauce. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in eggs; cook and stir until eggs are done, 4 to 5 minutes longer.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: microwave new england clam chowder
directions: Place potatoes, onion and clam juice in dish.
Cover. Microwave 7 to 9 minutes, until potatoes are fork-tender.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup milk; add to potatoes.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and stir.
Do not cover.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes, until thick; stir several times.
Stir in clams and light cream. Microwave 2 to 4 minutes, until hot.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Stir dry Jell-O into cottage cheese and let stand about 5 minutes, then add Cool Whip and fruit.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or more and serve.
Can use any flavor of Jell-O and any fruit.

title: orange muffins
directions: Combine orange pieces and juice in blender.
Puree.
Add dates, egg and oleo to blender.
Blend.
Pour into a medium bowl. Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and soda in separate bowl. Mix thoroughly.
Pour over top of orange mixture.
Stir to combine.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Yield: 12 large or 16 medium muffins.

title: mincemeat
directions: Pare, core and chop apples.
Combine with remaining ingredients; add water, cider or juice to moisten.
Simmer until meat and fruits are blended.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal. Any juice of your choice may be substituted.

title: heavenly frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour together in a saucepan until thick and comes to a paste.
Cool.
In a mixing bowl, cream sugar and oleo together until fluffy.
Add vanilla to the milk and flour paste, mixing well.
Add paste mixture to the creamed mixture and beat well until creamy consistency.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and mix. Drop by teaspoon on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: confetti rice
directions: In saucepan, brown rice with sage in butter.
Add broth. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Add peas. Simmer 10 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally.
Stir in pimiento.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: no cook divinity
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine dry frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat on highest speed of mixer until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to large bowl.
On low speed, gradually blend in sugar and nuts.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter together.
Heat and cook 1 minute. Add the peanut butter and vanilla. Combine oats with mixture. Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: marinated beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, but beans.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over beans.
(Sliced onions or bell peppers may be added, if desired.)
Refrigerate several hours before using.

title: fruit and macaroni salad
directions: Cook, drain and rinse acini de pepe macaroni #27.
Set aside. Drain fruit and save the juice.
To the juice, add 2 beaten eggs, sugar, pinch of salt and flour.
Mix well and cook until thick; be careful not to burn.
Add juice mixture to macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
Shortly before serving, add drained fruit and Cool Whip.

title: turkey broccoli bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in an 8 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In saucepan, melt the 2 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Swiss cheese until melted.
Stir in turkey.
Pour over broccoli. Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan and melted 1 tablespoon butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bananas and nuts, in a large bowl.
Add bananas and nuts right before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Heat sugar and juice in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in berries, orange pulp and peel.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add liqueur and simmer 2 minutes more.
Refrigerate covered.

title: oven baked candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes with brown sugar and pumpkin pie spice. Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine orange juice and vanilla. Add to the potatoes. Dot potatoes with butter. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove from oven and stir. Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes more or until potatoes are fork-tender. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: stuffed green pepper boats
directions: Remove seeds from peppers; parboil for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine rice, cheese and soup; stuff peppers with mixture. Place each pepper half in aluminum foil cup.
Place in baking pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips and drizzle with lemon juice and roll in dry sauce mix.
To get a smoked flavor, grill over charcoal for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender and done or you may add liquid smoke.
Serve with warm tortillas and toppings of your choice.

title: spaghetti
directions: Heat water.
Put noodles in water; bring to a boil in 15 to 20 minutes. Drain water off noodles; set aside.
Put the Ragu sauce and tomato paste in a boiler, stirring gradually until hot.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings, 250 calories per serving.

title: bill cleveland's taco soup
directions: Brown beef, dump fat, add onion and cook.
Add seasonings and mix.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until you can't wait any longer.

title: crabby's red velvet cake
directions: Mix vinegar and soda in small cup; let stand until settled. Cream sugar, eggs and shortening until light.
Make paste of cocoa and food coloring in cup.
Add paste to shortening mix; add buttermilk and salt alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Add soda and vinegar mixture.
Beat well.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) round pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut each layer in half to make 4 layers.

title: cinnamon rock candy by janis
directions: Combine sugar, Karo syrup, water and salt.
Cook in a medium saucepan to the hard rock stage (290°).
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring for pretty red color and cinnamon oil.
Pour in buttered pan until set, then break into pieces.
Delicious!

title: quik turkey pot pie
directions: Mix leftover turkey, soups, onion and seasonings.
(You can also add peas and carrots.)
Heat on stove for 10 minutes, then pour in pie crust.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk; stir for 2 minutes.
Pour over pie for the crust on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator rhubarb jelly
directions: Boil rhubarb, sugar and minimal amount of water for about 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir frequently.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Ladle carefully into hot jars.
Cool.
Apply lids to jars.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 2 to 3 months.

title: brenda's rolls
directions: Mix the yeast into the water.
Add the sugar and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together with a fork. Refrigerate overnight, then make dough into rolls and let them rise.
Bake at 325° to 350° until brown.

title: mary's pound cake
directions: Separate whites from yolks of eggs, beat yellows until very light.
Add sugar and beat until it is dissolved, then add softened butter.
Add flour that has been sifted with a pinch of salt.
Beat well, add flavoring and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 9-inch funnel pan, lined with wax paper, for about an hour and 15 minutes at moderate heat.
Test cake at an hour's baking with ice pick to determine balance of time needed for baking.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Beat 2 egg whites stiff.
Add sugar slowly, beating constantly.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet. Place in the oven and turn off heat.
Leave cookies in the oven overnight.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Barely cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch greased loaf baking dish.
Place boned, cooked chicken on top of broccoli.

title: vienna coffee
directions: Put 2 teaspoons in cup and add boiling water or to suit taste.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix Dream Whip and milk.
Set in refrigerator and chill.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix all together and put in pie shell.
Top with pie filling.

title: chocolate bundt cakedenver, colorado
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Put in greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan after it sets for 15 minutes.
(You can serve it hot also)

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Mix eggs, oil and buttermilk. Combine and mix well the two combinations.
Muffins can be baked now or stored in a covered container in the refrigerator to be baked as desired.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick butter and cracker crumbs together.
Pat into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and 2 sticks butter.
Beat for 15 minutes until creamy.
Pour over crumbs.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients except croutons and place in deep dish pie pan, then cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Prior to baking the next morning, sprinkle croutons on top of quiche.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: For crust, in a bowl, combine flour, nuts and brown sugar. Add melted butter; combine.
Spread mixture in shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spread 2/3 of the crust mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; set aside.

title: methodist cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered jar. Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Shake before serving.
Makes 1 1/4 cups dressing.

title: 4-h special
directions: Put onion and beef in skillet; cook over moderate heat.
Stir and turn until meat has browned.
Stir tomatoes, corn, rice and salt into meat.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange chiffon jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet.
Set until almost firm.
Add oranges.
Set until firm.
Can use 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: ham and cheese stuffing
directions: Boil weenies ahead of time and refrigerate until cold.
Grate weenies into bowl.
Grate cheese and a small amount of pickle into weenies.
Mix sweetener into mayonnaise.
This is just enough to sweeten the pickle.
Stir into weenie mixture.
Stuff celery. This equals 1 lunch protein, 1/2 beef and 1/2 cheese meal.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix package of pudding mix and can of pineapple.
Stir well. Add nuts, marshmallows and cherries. Mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip if desired.
Add green food coloring for green salad.
Pour into mold or bowl.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Saute onions in melted butter for 10 minutes in large kettle. Add flour to onions and butter and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring until flour is absorbed.

title: meringue
directions: Cook sugar, salt, water and cornstarch until thick; add to egg whites (hot).
Beat until it holds its peaks.
Cover pie filling. Bake in a 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press 1 entire package of sugar cookies onto cookie sheet with floured fingers after letting dough soften for 15 to 20 minutes at room temperature.
Mix the cream cheese with the powdered sugar and spread on cooled
crust.
Spread on strawberry glaze.
Add fruit, sliced.

title: salmon fillet - grilled
directions: Place salmon fillet in center of large piece of aluminum foil. Spread onion and Italian seasoning on top.
Dot with butter. Squeeze lemon over top.
Close foil.
Place on barbecue grill and cook until salmon is pink and flakes easily.
Do not overcook.

title: chocolate covered noodles
directions: Melt together milk, chocolate chips and butter. Bring to a boil.
Cook for about 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the noodles.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.
Let cool.
Enjoy!

title: ruthie's potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes and salt until tender; mash.
Cook the onion in the oleo until golden, then add flour.
Blend; add seasonings and milk in potatoes.
Cook until smooth.
Stir constantly.
Add wieners and serve.

title: tuna crunch
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup noodles.
In 1 1/2-quart pan, combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle on noodles around edges and bake 5 minutes more.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Line a large pie pan with dough.
Mix flour and 1/4 cup sugar together; spread over pie dough.
Add sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with vinegar or lemon juice.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar and allspice.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and bake at 375° to 400° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna cheese toasties
directions: Set oven to broil or 550°.
Broil bun halves 4 to 5 inches from heat until light brown.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Mix tuna, cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and horseradish.
Stir in beans.
Spoon about 1/2 cup tuna mixture onto each bun.
Sprinkle with American cheese.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: garden stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Microwave pierced potatoes on high for 12 minutes; bake for 15 minutes. Slice off potato tops. Scoop out pulp, keeping skins intact. Mash pulp in a medium bowl. Heat a small skillet over medium heat; add butter. Add onion and saute until tender, about 5 minutes. Add, broccoli, and salad dressing to potato pulp; mix well. Brush outside of potato skin shells with oil. Spoon potato mixture into shells, dividing evenly. Place on a baking sheet. Bake potatoes until heated through, about 15 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley; salt and pepper to taste.

title: vanilla drop cookies
directions: Combine shortening
and
sugar;
cream thoroughly.
Add beaten egg.
Sift
the dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture alternately
with
the milk and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet and bake in a moderate oven at 375° for
to
minutes.
Makes 50 cookies 1 1/2 inches in diameter.

title: s'more cookie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Press cookie dough into 2 ungreased 12-inch pizza pans. Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven. In medium-sized saucepan, melt chips with Eagle Brand milk. Spread over crust. Sprinkle with milk chocolate candies, marshmallows and pecans. Bake 4 minutes or until marshmallows are lightly toasted. Cool. Cut into wedges.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown the meat. Drain the grease from the meat.
Add all ingredients.
Simmer in a large crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cherry christmas tree cake
directions: The assembled cake is 9 x 26 inches long.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine in a large bowl the cake mixes, eggs, butter and orange juice.
Mix at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in grated peel and pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 15 minutes, then remove from pans.
Place completely cooled cakes upside-down and end to end.
Spread 2 cans frosting on top and sides.
Draw a Christmas tree shape and border in the frosting.

title: quick chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 11-inch pan and set aside.
In a 1-quart bowl, combine sugar and cocoa.
Cut butter into small pieces and dot over sugar mixture.
Stir in half and half and vanilla.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add butter; using a wooden spoon stir hot mixture until butter melts.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute until mixture loses its gloss.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour fudge into prepared greased dish and spread it evenly.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup nuts, lightly pressing them into fudge.
Refrigerate, uncovered, for 1 to 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store in tins or covered dish in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut avocados in half; remove pits and scoop the flesh out of the shells into a large bowl. Add lemon juice, Tabasco, onion, garlic, salt and pepper and toss well; use your hands. Using a sharp knife, slice through the avocados in the bowl until they are diced. Add the tomatoes. Mix well and taste for extra salt and pepper.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Put in Dutch oven to heat up.
Put cloves in orange slices in rind and let simmer.
Serve warm.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Add eggs and sugar.
Then add dates and nuts.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes. Remove from stove and add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Let cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 rolls.
Cool and slice.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Place crescent rolls on greased pizza pan.
Press seams together.
Spoon sausage over dough. Sprinkle potatoes and cheese over.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: oriental slaw
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the slaw mix, almonds, noodles, onions, sunflower seeds and set aside.
Combine oil, vinegar and sugar and mix well.
Pour over slaw mixture and toss.

title: wassail
directions: In large saucepan, heat cider and 1 cinnamon stick to boiling; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover; stir in remaining ingredients, except orange stars and cinnamon sticks, and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve in punch bowl.
Use cinnamon sticks as stirrers.

title: mexican party salad
directions: Cook meat (just until it loses its pink color).
Add onion; cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Mix salad ingredients together; toss gently.
Drain meat mixture and pour it over salad and serve.

title: silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth and fluffy (about 5 minutes on mixer so it won't be "grainy").
Melt chocolate over boiling water in double boiler.
Blend chocolate into butter-sugar mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and blend.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating 2 minutes after each addition.
Turn into baked pie shell and chill several hours.
Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: ice cream sauce
directions: Beat egg until thick and light.
Beat in sugar and salt. Gradually beat in butter extract.
Fold in cream.
Serve on warm chocolate or white cake squares.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: squash souffle
directions: Combine squash, onion and sugar.
Simmer with a small amount of water for 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Mash squash with a potato masher.
Add eggs, melted butter, flour, milk and cheese.
Add salt to taste.
Bake in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish for 30 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs and bake for 10 minutes more at 350°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and juice of 1 lemon.
Mix well.
Add chopped nuts and pineapple.
Then add Cool Whip.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in a graham cracker crust.
Let cool or chill but do not freeze.
Makes 2 pies.

title: diabetic strawberry pie
directions: Combine
grape juice, water and cornstarch in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until clear.
Mixture will not thicken. Remove from
heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Chill in bowl
in refrigerator
until
partially
set.
Stir in strawberries.
Spoon into
baked pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours or until set.

title: barbecue sauce(for chicken nuggets)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Cool.
Serve hot or cold.
Refrigerate any left overs.
Will keep for months.
Yields 1 pint.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls(kal rulletter)
directions: Remove and discard wilted outer leaves from cabbage.
Rinse and cut out core.
Put cabbage in kettle with boiling water to cover and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes, or until leaves are softened.
Carefully separate leaves and set aside on paper towels to drain.
Mix all other ingredients together for filling.
Place a small cabbage leaf in the center of a large one. Drop about 1/2 cup of filling into the center of each small leaf. (Filling will drop more readily from a moist spoon or cup.)
Roll each leaf, tucking ends in toward center.
Fasten securely with wooden picks or tie with clean string.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add chopped, fresh vegetables, then add salad dressing.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix often.

title: potato corn soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and carrots.
Boil in 3 cups water until cooked.
Mash slightly with potato masher.
Fry bacon and crumble into soup mixture.
Dice onion and saute in bacon drippings.
Add to soup mixture.
Add mushroom soup and creamed corn.
Simmer.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla.
Pour batter into 9-inch square baking dish.
Combine remaining sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa and salt.
Mix well and sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Also reheats well.

title: wheat germ muffins
directions: Beat together egg, sugar, milk and shortening.
Mix in flour, sifted with baking powder. Stir in wheat germ lightly. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 6 minutes. Remove from heat. Add margarine, vanilla and chips. Beat until creamy. Add nuts. Pour into greased pan. Cool.

title: chicken-ette
directions: Cook pepper, celery and onion with spaghetti.
Mix all the ingredients together and bake about 30 to 40 minutes in moderate oven or slow cook in a crock-pot a few hours.

title: date rolls
directions: Mix all well and form in loaf in crumbs.
Store in refrigerator overnight. Slice and serve.

title: macaroni 'n cheese italia
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine with sauce and water.
Place half of this mixture in the bottom of a 2-quart baking dish that's greased.
Top with half of the cottage cheese. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add layer of half of the cheese. Repeat next layer, ending with remaining cottage cheese, then shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: broccoli rice quiche
directions: Combine rice, 1 egg and 1/2 cup cheese, mixing well.
Press mixture into a greased 9-inch pie plate; set aside.
Cook broccoli and drain well.
Combine broccoli, 1/4 cup cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour broccoli mixture into rice-lined pie plate. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: phil's pound cake
directions: Dissolve soda in 1 tablespoon water.
Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Blend in flour, soda and buttermilk using low speed of electric mixer. Add lemon extract.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check after one hour until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: dilly cucumbers
directions: In a bowl combine oil, vinegar, dill and sugar.
Add cucumbers; stir well.
Refrigerate until serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the soda, flour, salt and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pans on rack until completely cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix items and put into baking dish.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Put crushed corn flakes on top.
Put half the butter on top of the casserole before putting on the corn flakes and the other half on top of the flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange-raisin breakfast cake
directions: Chop or grind raisins and orange rind. Set aside. Mix together orange juice and 1 cup sugar. Set aside. Cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs and blend. Add sour milk and blend. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Fold in the raisin and orange rind mixture. Bake in lightly greased and floured 9 X 13 cake pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Pour the sugar and orange juice mixture over the top of the cake immediately and return to the oven for a few more minutes to crystalize the sugar.

title: taco dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice.
Add salt and pepper.
Layer the ingredients as listed in an 8 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Serve with nachos.

title: oriental hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Mix soup and water together in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and hamburger to soup mixture.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover and cook until mixture is done.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jello dessert ii
directions: Mix both boxes of Jell-O with 3 cups boiling water. Add frozen strawberries and ice cream. Stir until dissolved. Pour over crumbled cake. Chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake for 20 minutes; cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cool cake.
Mix together pudding and cream cheese.
Add pineapple, walnuts and coconut.
Put on cake.

title: favorite pastry(2-crust pie)
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until particles are size of small peas.

Sprinkle in water one tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans side of bowl (1 to 2 teaspoons water can be added if necessary). Gather pastry into a ball.
Shape into flattened round on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Divide pastry in half and shape into two rounds.
Roll pastry 2-inches larger than inverted pie plate with floured cloth-covered rolling pin.
Fold pastry into fourths. Place in pie plate.
Unfold and ease into plate, pressing firmly against bottom and side.
Turn desired filling into pastry-lined pie plate.
Trim overhanging edge of pastry 1/2-inch from rim of plate.
Roll other round of pastry.
Fold into fourths and cut slits so steam can escape.
Place over filling and unfold.
Trim overhanging edge of pastry 1-inch from rim of plate.
Fold and roll top edge under lower edge, pressing on rim to seal.
Flute.

title: crisp bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice unpared cucumbers about 1/4-inch thick.
Add onions, peppers and salt.
Cover with ice water and crushed ice.
Mix well; let stand for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Pack cucumbers, peppers and onions in sterilized jars.
In a pan, add remaining ingredients; heat just to boil.
Pour over mixture in jars; add lids.
Cold pack for 25 minutes to assure sealing.
Yields about 8 pints.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 1 hour at 325°.

title: lo-cal soup
directions: Simmer all together for 1 hour.
Contains 30 calories.

title: cherry bread and butter pudding
directions: Cut crusts from bread.
Spread butter on one side of each slice.
Arrange four slices in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Spread about 2 teaspoons of preserves on each slice.
Repeat, making 2 more layers.

title: vidalia onion and spinach salad
directions: Place all in salad bowl.
Pour on favorite salad dressing and toss.

title: spinach and bacon salad
directions: Combine vinegar, soy sauce, salt, sugar, mustard, curry and pepper.
Add oil.
Shake well and chill.
Pour dressing over spinach.
Sprinkle with bacon and egg.
Yields 4 servings (150 calories per serving).

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add pineapple with its juice, pie filling and pecans. Refrigerate until firm.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Moisten potatoes with water.
Shake in a bag or roll in mixture of flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in single layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour; turn once. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine sauce and dressing together.
Mix everything together (except chips) in large container.
Pour dressing over mixture. Add chips just before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, pie filling and pineapple.
Add nuts and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Can be used as a salad or dessert.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and spread 1/2 tablespoon over chicken. Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.
May substitute ribs or pork for chicken.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine and beat 2 minutes the flour, baking powder, salt, butter, egg, milk and pudding.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie plate.
Drain peaches; place fruit on batter.
Beat for 2 minutes the cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons reserved liquid.
Spoon over fruit to within 1-inch edge of batter.
Sprinkle on top a mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Filling will appear soft but will set as it chills.

title: lasagne
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add hamburger and minced garlic; brown. Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, cook noodles.
Put alternate layers of noodles, Mozzarella, Ricotta, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese in greased pan or casserole.
End with meat sauce and grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until firm.
This recipe freezes well.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter. Add egg yolks.
Mix other ingredients and add stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 350° or 325° for 50 minutes or until done.
Bake in tube pan.
Do not ice.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Cream together white sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla to the sugar mixture.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar/egg batter, then add coconut, oatmeal, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet at once.
Yields 140 cookies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter the bread on one side.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk and salt thoroughly.
Pour over bread.
Top with ham.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken with purple plum sauce
directions: Begin early afternoon or previous evening!
Drain purple plums and save syrup.
Chop enough plums to make 1/2 cup.
Pit and halve the remaining plums.
Combine chopped plums, 1 cup of the syrup, soy sauce and scallions.
Stir in chicken.
Place in large, glass bowl and cover.
Marinate in refrigerator at least several hours.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Scoop out center of each roll.
Set aside.
Combine crabmeat and next 6 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into rolls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Cut beef in strips.
Mix garlic, soy sauce and ginger together with beef.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet, sprayed with Pam.
Add beef mixture.
Cook until beef is no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
Add veggies and stir-fry until tender.
Mix water and cornstarch.
Add to beef mixture in skillet.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 2.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown the sausage.
Cut biscuits into fourths and place in a medium sized casserole dish.
Spread the sausage over the biscuits.
Beat the eggs and pour over the biscuits and sausage. Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let sit for a few minutes before slicing.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides, place in casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place 4 rings of bell pepper on top of chops.
Place 1/2 onion in each pepper ring.
Add cooked rice on top of onion.
Pour canned tomatoes on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together and set aside.
Place oleo, shortening, cocoa and water in a saucepan and bring to a rapid boil.
Cool slightly and combine with flour and sugar mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into 16 x 11-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: italian spaghetti and meatballs with sauce
directions: Mix well and shape into small balls.
Brown good in salad oil.
Use same oil that you browned onions in.

title: italian sauce(for pizza)
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 3 hours or until sauce becomes thick.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine and add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix and pour over pretzels in 7x12x2 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool 25 minutes.
Mix well cream cheese and 1 c. sugar together. Prepare Dream Whip by package directions.
Fold in cream mixture. Spread over baked pretzels.
Combine gelatin with 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Chill slightly.
Top cream cheese layer with the strawberry mixture.
Chill until firm. Serves 20-24.

title: graham cracker snack
directions: Use cookie sheet with sides.
Place a layer of crackers on cookie sheet.
Boil brown sugar and butter for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool only 5 minutes and cut into squares.

title: tea balls
directions: Mix the flour and powdered sugar; add the butter, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Roll in some powdered sugar while still hot; then roll again in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate cake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place flour, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Put butter, water, shortening and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mix this with the dry ingredients. Mix together eggs, soda, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add to cocoa mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 15 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Begin making the icing about 5 minutes before cake is done.
Ice while cake is hot.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown onion and meat together; drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with corn chips, if desired.

title: oreo delight
directions: Melt the margarine in a small saucepan.
Mix all of the crushed Oreo cookies, except 1 cup, with the melted margarine. Press this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, beat the softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Then fold 6 ounces of the Cool Whip with this mixture.
Spread this mixture on top of the Oreo crust.

title: pizza pockets
directions: Spread pizza sauce on each slice of bread.
Put cheese on the bread.
Top with pepperoni.
Put bread on top.
Butter both sides and cook in toastmaster for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix margarine, milk, flour, pudding mix, egg and peach juice. Pour into casserole dish. Place peaches on top of batter. Mix sugar and cream cheese. Spoon on top of peaches. Sprinkle with cinnamon if desired. Put in 350° oven until done. This is done when brown around edges and edge is firm. The middle will be runny, but will set as it cools.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix thoroughly and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° if metal pan; if glass, bake at 325°.
Cool completely.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all the ingredients except potatoes in soup pot and cover with water.
Simmer until tender.
Add potatoes and other vegetables and a little more water to cover.
Add chicken flavoring as desired and cook until tender.

title: canned banana peppers
directions: Pack broccoli into jars. Add water to shoulder of the jar. Put seals on and process in pressure canner until pressure is 15 pounds. Turn off stove and let set until cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir in flour, salt and soda.
Add fruits and nuts.
Place mixture in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.
Insert toothpick in center; if it comes out clean, it is done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: streamline beef minestrone soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, beef broth, vegetables and pasta in large pot.
Bring to boil, reduce heat to medium and cook until pasta is tender, about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Meanwhile, combine ground beef and turkey, 2 tablespoons cheese, garlic powder and red pepper.
Form 24 meatballs with mixture and put on microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High 3 1/2 to 4 minutes, stir after 2 minutes.
Put meatballs in soup and stir to combine.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish with remaining cheese.
Yields 4 servings.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg, salt and vanilla.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Chill.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Blend in nuts and pineapple.
Spoon over pie and chill thoroughly.
Decorate top with halved maraschino cherries if desired.

title: bing cherry jello salad
directions: Use juice of cherries to make Jell-O.
To 1 cup of boiling water, add juice of cherries to make about 2 cups.
Let Jell-O set after adding cherries, pineapple and nuts.

title: cherry crunch cake
directions: Blueberry pie filling, strawberry pie filling or drained crushed pineapple may be used instead of cherries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Mix all other ingredients except crackers.

title: chicken and broccoli au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions and mushrooms.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, curry powder and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup water to flour mixture.
Blend milk into mixture until smooth. Cook and stir over moderate heat until sauce begins to thicken. Arrange broccoli and chicken on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly around edges.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place over high heat and add Tabasco. While mix is coming to a high boil, add coloring.
Stir in Certo.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil hard for one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and with metal spoon skim off foam.
Pour quickly into sterile jars.
Cover.
Makes 10 medium size glasses.
Great served with cream cheese on crackers.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix Nabasco 100% Bran, sugar, molasses, buttermilk, dates, raisins and nuts good.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda. Add to first mixture.

title: chocolate swirl cheese pie
directions: Add sugar to cheese in bowl, beating well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Measure 2 cups of cheese mixture; fold into chocolate.
Pour remaining cheese mixture into well-buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Add spoonfuls of chocolate and zigzag.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar; stir in egg and vanilla.
Shape in 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork to flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: knock you nekkids
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, pecans, 1/3 cup milk and melted butter. Press half of the batter into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 glass baking dish. Bake 8 minutes. Melt caramels with remaining 1/2 cup milk in microwave, stirring often, until smooth. Pour over baked layer. Cover with chocolate chips. Dot remaining batter on top. Bake 18 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In glass or stainless steel bowl, combine all ingredients except chicken; add chicken and toss to coat.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for at least 8 hours, occasionally tossing chicken in marinade.
Remove chicken from marinade; remove and discard garlic and ginger.
In blender container, process marinade.
Arrange chicken parts in disposable aluminum roasting pan; grill over hot coals until tender, basting occasionally with some of the marinade. Transfer chicken and pan juices to serving platter.
In small saucepan, bring remaining marinade to boil; serve with chicken. Makes 4 servings.

title: orange cream punch
directions: In a two gallon punch bowl, empty the orange sherbet.
Pour chilled 7-Up over sherbet and stir gently just until combined. Allow large chunks of sherbet to float on top of the punch.
Serve immediately.

title: macadamia nut pie crust
directions: Mix together in pie plate.
Heat 1 minute in microwave.
Stir up; heat 1 more minute; stir and heat 1 last minute.
Press into pie pan. Cool and fill with favorite filling.

title: kapok tree corn fritters
directions: Sift flour a second time with baking powder, sugar and salt. Add egg, milk and corn. Stir until well blended. Drop batter into hot fat a teaspoon at a time. Maintain fat to 350°. Fry until golden brown, turning once with spoon.
Remove fritters from fat; drain on paper towels. Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bisquick cheddar garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Mix bisquick, milk and shredded cheddar cheese together to form soft ball. Drop by 9 spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Mix butter and garlic powdered together and brush over warm biscuits. This mixture is sticky so can spray spoon with Pam.

title: ground beef pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt, chili powder and pepper; drain fat.
Place mixture in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour tomato juice over mixture.
Drain and place green beans on top of beef mixture.
Place mashed potatoes on top of green beans.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, butter and syrup.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat.
Pour over popcorn and stir to mix evenly.

title: raisin crisscross cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream margarine, sugar, egg white and flavoring together.
In another bowl, sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir well.
Mix in raisins.

title: kielbasa and potatoes
directions: Cut and start cooking potatoes.
In a large skillet, fry bacon until brown and crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Add onion to drippings and saute until golden brown.
Add potato cubes and stir over low heat until potatoes are lightly browned.
Cook kielbasa in boiling salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
If using sausages, brown on all sides in another skillet; cut into 1-inch slices.
(Fresh sausage works good.)
Add green or red peppers and stir over low heat for another 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pile on a serving platter and sprinkle with reserved crisp bacon.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef strips.
Add other ingredients, except sour cream. Add sour cream last.
Cook for 3 hours.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and 2 tablespoons sugar in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour or until jelled.
Add Cool Whip (thawed).
Break angel food cake in pan (half of it), then put a layer of topping, then another layer of cake and finally another layer of topping.

title: raspberry blossom dessert(prepare the day before)
directions: Boil water; pour into mixing bowl and add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add thawed raspberries and softened ice cream to gelatin mixture.
Stir until ice cream is completely melted.
Pour mixture into gelatin mold.
Refrigerate for several hours or until set.

title: deluxe chicken casserole
directions: Prepare noodle packets according to package directions.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Pour into a large casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave carrot cake
directions: Blend eggs and sugar.
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients (flour, salt, soda and cinnamon).
Add carrots and pecans.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Cook spareribs in water until nearly done.
Add bay leaf, onion, salt and pepper.
Add sauerkraut and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done.
A little cream may be added.
Half and half can be used.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Mix as for meat loaf.
Press in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Peel 8 medium potatoes; slice and cook until done.
Place on top of hamburger.
Add small can of cream of celery soup and 1 small can cream of mushroom soup.
Mix together and pour on top of potatoes. Add on top 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 or 9-inch casserole dish. Combine sweet potatoes, margarine, milk, sugar, egg and vanilla. Turn into prepared pan.
Combine brown sugar, pecans, flour and butter; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: * sauerkraut salad *
directions: This keeps in refrigerator for weeks.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place bread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown sausage and drain.
Sprinkle over bread.
Scramble eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° approximately 30 minutes.

title: 6 weeks muffins
directions: Combine Raisin Bran, sugar and flour with soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add mixture of eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Mix well. Refrigerate in a covered container for weeks if you wish.
Use batter when you want muffins in a hurry.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cake or pie glaze
directions: Stir together until smooth. Drizzle on while cake or pie is still warm.

title: ultimate brownie sundae
directions: Cut brownie into 6 equal pieces.
Set each piece on a dessert plate and top with a 1/2-cup size scoop of ice cream.
Ladle fudge sauce onto ice cream.

title: quick and easy beef stew
directions: Remove can of stew from cupboard, open with can opener.
Pour into saucepan (rinse out with a little water).
Heat thoroughly and eat.

title: easy hamburger dip
directions: Cook ground beef until done.
Drain.
Return to skillet and add cheese.
Cook on low until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Take out 1 cup and set aside for topping.
In remaining crumbs put in next 3 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Put 1 cup of crumbs that were set aside over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Line 9 x 13 inch pan with waxed paper.
Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into pan.
Pour dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture. Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and invert into serving platter.

title: grandma frances' perfect apple pie(yield: 8 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 425°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine and put in casserole dish.
Put on top of casserole 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Slice apples in a pan.
In another dish, mix together the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add the unbeaten egg; mix well.
Add oil; spread or crumble mixture over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is good and firm.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Fold in eggs.
Add vanilla and stir in oats.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients; put in buttered casserole dish. Melt margarine; mix with corn flakes (may substitute corn flake crumbs).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt hazel's johnny cake
directions: Stir egg and sugar.
In a separate bowl (and while holding over egg mixture bowl as it may bubble over), add soda to buttermilk.
Add buttermilk to egg mixture.
Add margarine and salt.
Stir in corn meal and flour.
Grease loaf pan, 5 x 8-inch shallow pan or muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes for loaf pan, 15 minutes for muffin tins or until inserted pick comes clean.
Serve hot, cold or toasted.
Can be frozen.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Dip tortillas in very hot water and line dish.
Add chicken and sprinkle about 3 tablespoons water over it.
Next, layer onion, pepper and cheese slices.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over all.
Pour heated cream of mushroom soup over tomatoes and sprinkle with chili powder.
Bake in oven 30 minutes, uncovered. Makes 9 large servings.

title: eggs and sausage
directions: Mix, pour into baking dish and bake.
May be prepared the night before and refrigerated.
Bake at 340° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Prepare, bake and cool pastry shell.
Mix softened butter, sugar and chocolate (melt chocolate over hot water or on very low heat to keep from sticking).
Add eggs, one at a time and vanilla. You will need an electric mixer for this; do not try without. Whip cream; sweeten as desired.
Top chocolate mixture with whipped cream.
Grate chocolate on top.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blender salad dressing
directions: Blend ingredients in blender until smooth.
Store in refrigerator and stir well before serving.

title: quick and sassy pork chops
directions: Cut lemon in half and rub lemon pulp on pork chops.
Rinse lemon pulp off and dry pork chops with paper towel.
Heat olive oil in saucepan.
Season chops with salt, pepper, sage and garlic. Place chops in pan and sear for 3 minutes on each side.
Add chopped onions and peppers and let chops cook for 2 additional minutes on each side.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry delite
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions; chill.
In large bowl, tear angel food cake into pieces.
Pour pineapple and pie filling over cake; mix together.
Top and spread with pudding, then top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with pecans and fresh strawberries.
Can substitute with any flavor pie filling. Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Can double; great for showers or wedding parties made in punch bowl.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix well and put in refrigerator overnight.
Make into balls and put in icebox for 30 minutes.
Melt 1 large package paraffin. Dip the balls into the chocolate and set on wax paper.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Blend all of the ingredients.
Let set overnight if you can. Warm up in the oven and serve with crackers, etc.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add beaten egg and applesauce.
Sift flour before measuring.
Use a little of the same flour to sift over fruit and nuts.
Sift remaining flour with salt and spices.
Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Add the flour mixture to creamed mixture, then add soda and boiling water.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer (medium speed).
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake in Bundt pan (greased and floured) for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 20 minutes in pan before turning out on plate.

title: 24-hour vegetable salad
directions: In bottom of a large glass bowl, place 3 cups of the lettuce. Sprinkle with a little sugar, pepper and salt.
Layer eggs atop lettuce, standing the ones on side of bowl on edge to look nice. Sprinkle generously with salt.
Next, layer in order:
peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread Miracle Whip over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours or overnight.
Garnish with sliced green onion and paprika, if desired.
Toss before serving.
Makes about 15 servings.

title: meatballs with sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Brown meatballs and pour off fat.
Add 1 (12 ounce) bottle of chili sauce and 1 (10 ounce) jar grape jelly.
Stir until melted.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Mix sugar, salt and soda together, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir in flour carefully and slow.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: glenn's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in greased oblong pan, iron skillet or muffin tins at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned chow chow
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and bring to a boil, then reduce heat and cook for 20 to 25 minutes. Put in pint jars and seal. Yields 8 to 9 pints.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Mix juice, flour, egg, vinegar and sugar in saucepan.
Cook mixture over very low heat until thickened.
Cool.
Add drained pineapple and cheese to mixture.
Add marshmallows just before serving.

title: raisin sauce for baked ham
directions: In saucepan, cook raisins and water for 10 minutes over medium heat.
Mix all other ingredients together and add to raisins. Cook until thick.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer all
ingredients and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 6 in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: white chili
directions: Put beans in Dutch oven. Cover. Bring to boil. Reduce and simmer 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixer bowl; beat on medium speed 1/2 minute, scraping side and bottom of bowl.

title: bacon dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Stir in bacon.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 2/3 cup sugar into egg yolks.
Add salt; stir in milk and evaporated milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 6 tablespoons of sugar, beating to soft peaks.
Add to custard and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla. Serve hot.
Dash with nutmeg.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions; drain.
Add tomato sauce and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Simmer and serve.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter until it is fluffy.
Add sugar by tablespoons.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Beat the egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Add the sour cream and flour to the butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flavorings and salt.
Mix thoroughly. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat meat, vegetables and gravy thoroughly.
Pour into greased casserole.
Combine potatoes and egg.
Make a border with potato mix over meat mixture or cover it completely.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until top is light brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Chill in original bowl.
Form a ball.
Roll in 1 1/2 tablespoons Parkay and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: white chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well.
By hand, add remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool on sheet for 1 minute. Then remove.

title: german potato salad
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Blend in flour and stir in vinegar and water.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over sliced, cooked potatoes.
Let flavors blend for 6 to 8 hours in refrigerator.

title: broccoli and lima bean casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and lima beans according to directions on packages; drain well.
Mix vegetables with soup and cheese. Pour into 9 x 13 well greased casserole dish. Cover with crushed Fritos. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Add 1/2 the sugar slowly, beating constantly.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add remaining sugar gradually.
Continue to beat until holds a soft peak.
Add lemon juice and rind, fold gently into beaten egg whites.
Combine flour and salt, fold it into egg mixture.
Put wax paper into an 11 x 16-inch shallow pan to line. Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, don't overbake.
Turn cake out on a clean towel, sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Remove paper and trim off crusts.
Roll, lifting towel nearest you. When cool, unroll and spread with jelly and roll again.
Really good with lemon jello pie filling or make up your own filling.

title: zucchini sausage bake
directions: In skillet, brown sausage, breaking up into small pieces; drain.
Toss with 1 tablespoon flour.
Spread on bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
In same skillet, cook zucchini and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Toss with remaining flour. Spoon half of zucchini mixture over meat.
In bowl, mix cottage cheese, Italian cheese, eggs and garlic salt.
Spoon evenly over zucchini later.
Top with remaining zucchini.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cheddar.
Bake 2 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Dip chicken in egg and then into crumb mix. Preheat electric skillet to 350° and melt butter in skillet. Cook chicken breasts about 3 minutes on each side. Combine tomato sauce, tomatoes and water. Pour over chicken. Reduce heat to 220°; cover and cook 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top; cover and cook until cheese melts.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in pan; add water. Cook until thickens. Add egg yolks to small amount of hot mixture in a dish, then add to mixture in pan. Boil 1 minute. Add lemon juice and butter; boil 1 or 2 minutes. Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake. Use the egg whites for meringue.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut top from the peppers; remove carefully all the seeds and tongue.
Cut thin slices from the bottoms so the peppers will stand.
Melt the butter, add the flour and seasoning, then the milk and onion juice; add the meat and fill the peppers with the mixture.
Cover with crumbs made by stirring 2/3 cup bread crumbs into 2/3 tablespoon of melted butter.
Place the peppers in a baking pan and cover the bottom with boiling water.
Bake in a moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Pour apple juice concentrate in a saucepan, stirring well. Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in margarine, cinnamon and vanilla extract.
Add apples; toss well to coat.
Pour into a pastry shell.
Cover top with crust.
(Slit to allow steam to escape.)
Trim edge around pie pan.
Seal crust. Flute edge.
Cover edge with strips of aluminum foil.
Bake at 420° until crust is brown (40 to 50 minutes).
Remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.

title: orange julius
directions: Put into blender until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: big minnie breakfast
directions: Slice pitas into halves.
Mix eggs, cheese, bacon bits or meat, green pepper, tomato and milk.
Pour mixture into lightly oiled skillet and cook on low heat.
Fill 4 pita halves with filling. Eat and enjoy!

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Slice apples; mix with 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Put mixture in pie plate.
Mix crumbs by mixing 1/2 cup sugar and 3/4 cup flour together.
Cut butter into flour and sugar.
Sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: fruit tree bug repellent
directions: Put all ingredients in plastic bag.
Hang on lowest limb of any fruit tree.
Guaranteed to work.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Bring to a boil the oil, vinegar, salt, mustard and celery seed.
Pour over cabbage.
Let set 4 hours in refrigerator.
The longer it sets, the better it gets.

title: how to be a good neighbor
directions: Blend all together; form into one being and serve generous portions daily to everyone you meet.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and mash with fork, add other ingredients and mix well with spoon.
Put in baking dish or pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot with Wheat Thins or similar cracker.

title: make ahead layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, carrots, peas, celery, onions and parsley.
Add the following:
sour cream, mayonnaise and bacon bits.
Mix mayo and sour cream.
Spread on top and top with bacon bits.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine light corn syrup, water and sugar.
Boil to 265° (hard ball stage).
Beat egg whites stiff and gradually beat in boiling syrup.
Whip until it begins to stiffen.
Add vanilla and pecans. Drop on waxed paper.
Makes about 150 pieces.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and turn into 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake until rice and chicken are tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
During cooking, add water if necessary to keep rice moist.

title: slow-cooked swiss steak
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Add the steak; seal bag and toss to coat.
Place the onion in a greased slow cooker.
Top with the steak, celery and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook on low for 6 - 8 hours, or until meat is tender.
Yields:
6 servings.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes only.
Do not overbake.

title: laverne's beef stew
directions: Brown beef in heavy Dutch oven in olive oil. Brown onion.
Add about 3 cups water, bay leaves, bouillon cubes and seasonings. Cook about 20 minutes.
Add carrots and cook about 20 minutes. Add celery and other ingredients except potatoes, soup and peas. Last, add the potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Add soup and some water.
Last add peas.
Serve with toasted English muffins.

title: pizza dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream and all spices together.
Spread on bottom of pie plate or quiche dish.
Pour on pizza sauce.
Top with peppers, scallions and pepperoni.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella over all.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with plain tortilla chips.
This recipe came from my sister-in-law, Nicole Plinck.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in round thin slices.
Spray a casserole dish or butter it well.
Layer potatoes and chopped onions.
Mix Cheddar cheese soup and milk in a bowl.
Soup will still be undissolved.
Pour this mixture over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dot top with butter.
Cover with foil lightly to keep top from getting too brown.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: celery cranberry relish
directions: Grind all ingredients using coarse blade of food chopper or grinder.
Chill.
Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks. Makes 4 cups.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: In bowl, cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over cooled brownies.

title: donna's lemon pound cake
directions: Cream cream cheese until soft.
Add eggs to cream cheese and beat well.
Add lemon cake mix (not the pudding variety) and 3/4 cup of milk, blending well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9-inch tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° without opening the oven door.
Bake another 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: sweet pickled peaches
directions: Mix vinegar, water, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Drop in whole fresh peaches which has been peeled.
Simmer peaches in syrup for about 5 minutes.
Pack in warm clean jars and pour syrup over them. Seal.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt and water.
Cook stirring constantly till sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking till ball forms when dropped into cool water.
Beat egg whites till stiff-pour 1/2 of syrup into egg whites and beat.
Cook remaining syrup to thread forms in cool water.
Add to first mix and beat till hold shape.
Add nuts and vanilla. Drop by spoonsful onto wax paper.
Let cool and dry-turn candies over and dry on other side. Store in air tight container in dry place.

title: caramel squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and mix well in saucepan.
Let bubble until sugar dissolves.
Take off heat.
Add eggs.
Beat so eggs do not cook.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour this mixture over the corn flakes and coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs. Gradually add powdered sugar.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over peanut mixture.
Let cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Can be made in microwave.

title: cucumber dip
directions: *Add more mayonnaise if needed for dip consistency.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Put milk and butter in top of double boiler to heat.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add sugar and beat vigorously.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into egg mixture and add vanilla.
Add hot milk mixture stirring constantly.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Combine icing ingredients and spread on warm cake and return to oven until frosting caramelizes but not long enough to dry it out.

title: joan's lime gelatin
directions: In large bowl, stir gelatin and boiling water until dissolved. In blender, whip cream cheese and cold water until smooth, then add to gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into gelatin mold and chill until set.

title: fruit bavarian
directions: Soak gelatin
in
cup cold water.	Drain the fruit well. Reserve
cup of the juice, adding water, if necessary.
Heat. Stir in the gelatin until dissolved.
Add fruit. Chill.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat in oil the onions and peppers.
Brown hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Put grated cheese on top. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: swedish pot roast
directions: Combine nutmeg, cinnamon, ginger, salt and pepper.
Rub into meat. Brown meat in oil.
In crock-pot, combine onion, garlic and brown sugar. Dissolve in wine, water and bay leaves.
Add meat, potatoes, carrots, etc.
Cook on high 4 to 5 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in saucepan, then add other ingredients.
Serve over any meats.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chocolate chips, grated chocolate bar and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: butterscotch trifle
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package, adding rum flavoring. Slice cake into 1/2-inch slices and line the bottom of an oblong baking dish.
Pour pudding over cake and spread evenly.
Slice bananas and cover pudding layer.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over banana layer.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
