Serve with whipped topping.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: angel food cake
directions: Put empty 10-inch tube pan in a hot oven (425°).
Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in sifted granulated sugar 2 tablespoons at a time.
Sift confectioners sugar and cake flour together 5 times.
Fold into egg white mixture 2 tablespoons at a time.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Remove pan from oven; pour batter immediately into hot pan.
Bake in hot oven (425°) exactly 23 minutes; don't peek. Remove from oven.
Place upside down on a cake rack.
Remove from pan when cooled.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, egg, vanilla, water and peanut butter.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well. Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes over 5 dozen.

title: low-fat raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix together Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt. Add eggs, applesauce, buttermilk and golden raisins.
Mix well. Spray muffin tins with cooking spray, or use paper cups.
Fill 3/4 full with batter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.
(Using the "Egg Beaters" instead of real eggs is what makes the muffins low-fat.)

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with your choice of bread pieces, raw vegetable or crackers.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook and stir in meat in Dutch oven until light brown.
Spoon off fat.
Add onions, cabbage and celery.
Cook and stir until vegetables are light brown.
Stir in tomatoes and seasonings. Cover tightly; simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in beans (with liquid); heat until mixture boils.
Simmer uncovered 15 to 20 minutes.
Top stew with mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash.
Add the cheese, mustard, few grains pepper and enough milk to moisten well.
Beat until fluffy and refill the egg whites.
Garnish with paprika for added color.

title: moussaka
directions: Slice eggplant; sprinkle with salt.
Set aside for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pare and slice potatoes.
Dry eggplant slices.
Saute eggplant and potato slices in olive oil until browned.
Drain on paper towel; set aside.
Saute onion and ground beef in 2 tablespoons melted butter until brown.
Add parsley and tomato sauce; simmer for 10 minutes.
Dust a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with bread crumbs.
Place a layer of potatoes, eggplant and beef mixture in dish.
Repeat layers ending with eggplant. Combine 4 tablespoons remaining butter and flour in saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg yolks; combine with cheese and nutmeg.
Stir slowly into sauce. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into sauce.
Pour sauce over top of eggplant.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Salt and pepper to taste enough cracker crumbs to make firm. Mix ingredients all together and form loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix first 6 ingredients in medium bowl. In a large bowl, combine pumpkin and oil; add eggs.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Place zucchini and onion in saucepan and cover with water. Boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Mix carrots, cream cheese and chicken soup.
Add zucchini and onion.
Mix herb dressing mix with melted butter until well blended.
Layer 2/3 of the crumb mixture at the bottom of a 10 x 9-inch dish.
Pour filling over crumb mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour or 45 minutes until golden brown on top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread into a greased and floured pan, 13 x 9-inch; bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in medium microwavable bowl on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly in crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until chocolate is firm.
Arrange banana slices over chocolate.

title: peach four layer dessert
directions: Melt butter in long cake pan.
Mix in flour and nuts.
I like 2 cups graham cracker crumbs instead of flour.
Spread out in pan to form crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Soften cream cheese; blend in powdered sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thickens.
Add peach jello.
Stir and cool.
Slice peaches over cream cheese.
Pour jello mixture over peaches.
Refrigerate until sets slightly.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add nuts, apple and vanilla.
Makes 1 (8-inch square pan).
Double recipe for 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: strawberry freeze
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch dish and freeze.
Set out 20 minutes before serving.

title: white bread(12 loaves)
directions: Cook potatoes; put through sieve.
Dissolve yeast in water with a little sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead.
Let rise, etc.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and orange slices.
Mix all together and chill.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 of the butter.
Press half of mix in greased baking pan.
If desired, put other half on top and cover with rhubarb.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, vanilla and water.
Pour over cake.
Top with remaining crumbles and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: waldorf salad dressing
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook and debone chicken and chop.
Chop pickles, celery and add Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Add salt and pepper.
If it's dry you can add pickle juice or chicken broth.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.
You can freeze it.

title: cherry goodie
directions: Cream the cheese with sugar and almond extract.
Crush pretzels and add melted oleo.
Put pretzel mix in 8-inch pan and spread out.
Put cream cheese on top of pretzels, then put pie filling on top.
Add topping.
Make a day before serving.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl and mix with an electric
mixer	on
medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased
9	x
13-inch
pan.
Drain
peach	slices	and reserve juice.
Gently arrange peach slices on batter, leaving a 3/4-inch space
around
the	edge of the pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and
peach juice and mix 2 minutes with mixer on medium
speed. Carefully
spread
cream
cheese
mixture over peaches without touching sides of the pan but be sure to cover all	peaches completely.
Sprinkle
cinnamon
and
sugar over cream cheese mixture.
Bake
30	to
40 minutes in a 350° oven until top turns golden brown.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, lemon juice, egg and margarine.
Stir in grated apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: barbecue relish
directions: Grind vegetables and apples through coarse blade of food grinder.
Combine sugar, salt, spices and vinegar.
Pour liquid over mixture and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Pack into jars and seal.

title: grandma's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and milk and pour over sliced bread. Dip each piece of bread in beaten eggs, handling carefully so that bread retains its shape.
Gently melt butter in a skillet and fry bread on both sides until golden brown.
Remove to serving dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar (pre-mixed).
Serve hot.

title: the best whoopie pies!
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add dry mixture, alternately with sour milk.
Mix hot water and cocoa to make a paste. Blend into rest of mixture.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Remove egg yolks from eggs.
Mash and add relish, crumbled bacon, bacon drippings, mustard, salt and pepper to taste and enough mayonnaise to mix well.
Fill egg halves.
If desired, sprinkle paprika over eggs.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening, and sugar until light and fluffy, add eggs, (which have been beaten until lemon colored). Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk. Stir in flavorings. Spoon mixture into greased 10 inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Cool in pan about 10 minutes before turning on rack to cool.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Using a food processor, mix graham crackers to desired consistency (net 2 cups).
Place in mixing bowl.
Melt the spread and add into graham crackers and mix by hand using a fork, blending together until sticky and completely blended.
Put mixture into pie plate and form into crust.
Place in freeze to harden.
(There may be some mixture leftover to add on top, if desired.)
Makes enough for one 8-inch diameter by 1 inch deep pie plate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand at least 30 minutes before baking.
Pour into greased glass pan; bake until golden brown. Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake your favorite cake recipe.
Let marshmallows melt over medium heat in 1 cup milk and 1 cup sugar.
Add coconut.
Put this between layers.
Combine 2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup milk, margarine and cocoa.
Let boil real hard for 1 minute.
Beat well until it begins to fudge.
Put on top and sides.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in top of double boiler or microwave, stirring often. Put cereal, pecans and marshmallows in large warm bow. Quickly add melted almond bark. Mix well and drop in balls on waxed paper or cookie sheet. Store in refrigerator.

title: butter brickle cookies
directions: Mix and drop. Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 minutes or until done.

title: scalloped pineapple(a great side-dish for special dinners)
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo; beat in eggs.
Add milk, pineapple and bread cubes.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole (9 x 13-inch, etc.).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Blend well.
Salt to taste. Spread on cracker.

title: broiled trout
directions: After a successful day of fishing, prepare trout in the following manner:

title: no fat no sugar carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; store in refrigerator.
Keeps several days.

title: linguini salad
directions: Sprinkle Parmesan on top and toss.

title: microwave stewed corn and tomatoes(indian style)
directions: Melt butter in a 3-quart dish.	Saute onion, pepper and garlic on High
3 minutes or until tender.
Add corn, tomatoes and salt. Cover and
cook
on
High 20 minutes.
Stir once or twice. Cooking
time
will
be
shorter if using canned corn. You	can add
pound cooked shrimp during last 5 minutes of cooking if desired.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill and serve.

title: meringue candy canes
directions: Beat together the egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla in large bowl until foamy, using electric mixer at high speed. Gradually add sugar; continue beating until stiff peaks form. Tint pink with red food coloring.
Fill a large pastry bag fitted with a medium star tip (#4) with meringue mixture.
Pipe mixture into 3 1/2-inch long candy canes, about 1 inch apart, on baking sheets covered with brown paper.
Sprinkle each with red sugar. Bake in a 275° oven for 45 minutes, or until set, but not browned.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Place half the bread cubes in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cream cheese cubes, blueberries and remaining bread.
Beat together eggs, syrup and milk; pour evenly over bread.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake covered with foil for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 15 to 30 minutes until top is golden and crunchy. Serve warm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: dolly's cookies
directions: Put margarine in large bowl.
Add sugar and cream together. Add 2 cups flour and baking powder at a time until you use all 6 cups.
Add all eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
(Sometimes you may have to add extra flour.)
Knead dough until smooth.
Shape cookie about 3 inches long.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
When cookie cools down, dip cookie in confectioners sugar and water.

title: green beans and water chestnuts with sour cream and herb sauce
directions: Clean and cut green beans into 1-inch pieces.
Cook beans and drain.
Slice water chestnuts.
Saute onion in butter until golden.
Add herbs, seasonings, sour cream and milk.
Heat, but do not boil.
Combine beans, water chestnuts and onion mixture into a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until crumbs are nicely browned.
Serves 8.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix
and bring to boil; stir in baking soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake in 300° oven for a few minutes.
Stir often while
in oven.
Stir
while
cooling down often, so it won't stick together in clumps.

title: spicy rice(yields 6 servings)
directions: Slice sausages crosswise into bite-sized chunks and brown in large, heavy bottomed pot.
Add seasonings and rice.
Mix well to coat rice.
Add water; mix and bring to boil.
Add frozen vegetables and leave on top of rice.
Cover; lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Check pot.
If rice isn't completely done, continue cooking for 5 to 10 more minutes, adding hot water if necessary to keep pot from scorching.
When rice is done, or very nearly so, remove from heat.
Fluff with fork to mix in vegetables, then cover and let set for at least 5 minutes before serving.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Gradually add water, stirring with a fork.
The dough will be crumbly.

title: chili roasted chicken wings(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Toss chicken wings in the lemon juice and garlic.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Set aside 1 tablespoon spice mixture.
Rub the greater portion of the spices onto the wings, distributing them evenly.
Place the wings in a single layer to marinate 2 to 12 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove wings from marinade and place on lightly greased foil covered rimmed cookie sheet.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle on the reserved spices and bake another 10 minutes.
Nice and spicy, but not too hot!

title: tangy orange cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Serve at room temperature with gingersnaps (i.e., Swedish gingersnaps).

title: wonderful mustard sauce
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch, dry mustard and salt.
Beat the eggs,
water and vinegar together with a hand mixer.
Combine all ingredients in a double boiler or small saucepan.
When all are combined, cook over low heat and stir often.
Keep in refrigerator until thick.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Beef and bell pepper must be chopped fine.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine water and cornstarch; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat until hot (3 to 5 minutes).
Stir in cornstarch until sauce thickens slightly (about 2 minutes).
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sausage bread squares
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
In a bowl combine sausage mixture with cheese, egg and seasonings.
Make dough with Bisquick, milk and mayonnaise.
Divide dough in half.
Press half of dough in well greased 8-inch square pan.
Cover with sausage mixture.
Put remaining half of dough on top.
Brush with a beaten egg yolk.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut into small squares and serve warm.
Good with breakfast, for a morning coffee or as hors d'oeuvres.

title: gravy
directions: Mix flour and water in covered jar.
Shake until smooth.
Add to meat drippings. Stir until smooth.
On low heat, bring to simmer for a few minutes.
Keep stirring. Add garlic powder, salt and pepper while cooking.
(Adjust seasonings to taste.)
You may add a few drops Gravy Master for darker color.

title: tuna ball or spread
directions: Mix all together and shape into a ball or use like a spread. Chill overnight.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except sour cream and Cool Whip. Mix sour cream and Cool Whip together and fold into first mixture. Freeze several hours before serving.
Double for a large dish.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well. Add the kraut, rinsed and drained. Add the green pepper, celery and pimento.

title: basic fried rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Stir-fry pepper and onion one minute.
Add soy sauce and rice.
Cook and stir until hot.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix tomatoes, bread, pepper, celery salt and brown sugar together and pour into buttered casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fish chowder
directions: Bring water to a boil in a Dutch oven.
Add potatoes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Fry salt pork until transparent.
Add onion and cook until onion is soft and salt pork is lightly browned. Add salt pork, drippings, fish fillets, thyme and marjoram to potatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in half and half, salt and pepper; simmer 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix first three ingredients with a mixer.
Drain pimientos, olives and chilies in a strainer, pressing out liquid with a paper towel.
Place a tortilla on a large square of plastic wrap. Spread with 1/4 of the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/4 of the vegetables.
Roll up as tightly and evenly as possible.
Roll and seal well in the plastic wrap.
Repeat with remaining tortillas. Chill at least 2 hours.
Unwrap and cut into 1-inch slices. Discard ends.
Serve with spirals facing up.
Makes 3 dozen.
May serve with hot sauce.
You can add thin slices of salami, turkey or ham.

title: pecan chess bars (beach cake)
directions: Mix with electric mixer and pour over top of crust. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cuts better when cooled real well. I refrigerate overnight before cutting.

title: fudge pie like brownies
directions: Melt butter in	a pot.	Add sugar and cocoa; mix quickly.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake in greased pie pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot and sour chicken wings
directions: Combine chicken wings, soy sauce and lemon juice in bowl; stir to blend.
Cover and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
On broiler pan, place chicken wings and broil 6 inches from heat, basting occasionally with marinade, until golden brown on both sides.
While chicken is broiling, combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to slow boil, stirring constantly, to dissolve sugar.
Continue boiling until sauce bubbles.
On platter, pour a thin coating of sauce.
Place chicken on top.
Pour remaining sauce over all.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Melt butter; add hamburger, stir until browned.
Stir in salt, pepper, basil and tomato sauce.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Combine spaghetti with cottage cheese.
Place 1/2 spaghetti mixture in 1-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat with spaghetti and meat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: penne d'allessandria(serves 4)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place pepper slices in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and drizzle with 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake until peppers are charred on edges and tender, stirring occasionally (30 to 40 minutes).
Remove from oven.
Finely chop parsley, oregano, thyme and garlic together and set aside.
Saute mushrooms in 3 tablespoons olive oil until tender.
Add chopped herbs and stir for 2 minutes.
Transfer to side dish and wipe out skillet.

title: chickpea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Mix together and add broth to moisten dough.
Work flour in as making biscuits until stiff.
Roll out and let set to dry for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drop in rolling boiling liquid broth, then turn to low and simmer until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer with salt and pepper until tender.
Don't use much salt or broth will be too salty to mix in dressing.
Take meat off bone and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Put cream of chicken soup over chicken and 1/2 soup can of broth from the chicken.
Mix stuffing, butter or margarine and 1 soup can of chicken broth. Put on top of chicken.
Cook at 350° until it begins to boil, then turn on broil until nice and brown.

title: hot cinnamon bread(8 servings)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add spices and flour.
Mix well. Reserve 3/4 cup of this mixture for the top.
To the rest, add egg, buttermilk, etc.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 2-quart ovenproof glass baking dish.
Cover top with crumbles. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with butter.

title: sand tarts
directions: Combine and form into 4 balls.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, soften ball with warmth of hands.
Roll very thin.
Cut out and decorate.
Bake at 400°. Watch closely, they brown quickly!

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: Pile mashed potatoes in baking dish.
Beat 1/2 cup of heavy cream until stiff.
Fold in 1/2 cup of grated cheese and season with salt and pepper.
Spread over the potatoes and bake in oven (350°) until delicately brown, 15 minutes or so.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples in pie shell.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and spread over apples.
Mix flour, sugar and melted butter.
Spread on top. Bake 10 minutes at 400°; reduce to 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti in oiled water until tender.
Combine all chopped ingredients.
Pepper to taste and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Drain spaghetti; mix with chopped mixture and pour bottle of Italian salad dressing.

title: stack ups
directions: To the browned and drained hamburger, add taco mix and water. Simmer 15 minutes.
Stack ingredients starting with Fritos, then meat, beans, lettuce and cheese.
Top with picante sauce.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni (on box).
Cook and stir margarine, onion, salt and pepper over medium heat until onion is tender.
Blend in flour. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth. Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese. Stir with macaroni.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies(no eggs)
directions: Mix together.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 90 cookies.

title: turkey wild rice soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until crisp-tender.
Add turkey, both packets from rice mix, water and chicken bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Stir; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Add broccoli and carrot.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes more.
Stir in half and half.
Heat to serving temperature; do not boil.
Stir in sherry, salt and pepper to taste.

title: butter rich cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 2 of the eggs and pat into 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: herb roasted orange salmon
directions: In a bowl or Ziploc bag, mix marinade. Combine the olive oil, orange juice, orange zest, garlic, tarragon, salt and pepper.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Cut cheese in cubes; set aside.
Cook ground beef until brown. Drain well.
Add cheese and chili to ground beef.
Cook over low heat until cheese is all melted.
Stir constantly to keep from sticking.

title: jubilee jumboes
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in evaporated milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and stir in mixture.
Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and cook about 12 minutes at 357°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour and set aside.
In saucepan, heat milk and egg yolks, then add sugar, cocoa and flour mixture.
When done, add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with Cool Whip.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Make sauce of all ingredients, except the vegetables. Marinate overnight; pour over chopped vegetables just before serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef stew meat (optional) and cook in water.
Add noodles or barley cereal at this time, until done.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugars, eggs, margarine and vanilla. Cream together and then add dry ingredients.
Spread onto greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 2 cups chocolate chips over surface.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 5 minutes. Remove pan from oven and run knife through batter to marble.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: acorn squash with applesauce
directions: Scrub, halve lengthwise and remove seeds from squash.
Mix remaining ingredients, except butter.
Put mixture into squash halves; dot with butter.

title: country cheese snacks
directions: Combine and spread on rye bread, bagels or English muffins. Broil until golden and bubbly.
Place stuffed green olives on top and serve hot.

title: baked butter beans
directions: Drain beans; let bean liquid settle and then measure 1/4 cup of the clear liquid and reserve.
In
a medium skillet, melt butter; add onion and green pepper and cook until wilted.
Stir in mustard, sugar and vinegar, then tomato soup and reserved 1/4 cup bean liquid.
Heat.
Turn beans into a 1-quart casserole; pour the tomato sauce over them.
Put bacon slices on top of this if desired.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 45 minutes or longer if you want them cooked down more.

title: golden lemon cheese pie
directions: In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with Golden Lemon Topping.
Chill 3 hours.

title: 7 up lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, beat in cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, sugar & nuts, add 7 Up. Chill until set.

title: congo bars
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Stir in butter, vanilla and eggs.
Blend in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 20 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, syrup and water in heavy-bottom kettle.
Cook and stir until 250°.
Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to 300°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda; fold through, stirring just enough to mix in.
Pour onto greased cookie sheets to cool.
Do not spread.
When cold, break in pieces.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash as many sweet potatoes as you want.
Cool.
Make two balls and put one marshmallow inside.
Roll in coconut, then finely chopped pecans.
Put in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mince salmon and add to it stale bread crumbs, well beaten egg and milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
A little onion improves the flavor.
Bake 30 minutes in a loaf pan.

title: brandied hot dogs(snack)
directions: Cut hot dogs in pieces (or small links).
Simmer in crock-pot 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Mix gelatine with 1/4 cup water; set aside.
Mix together 4 egg yolks with 1/2 cup lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add gelatine mixture.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add 2 drops yellow food coloring and 1 tablespoon grated lemon rind. Cool.
Beat 4 egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until they peak; then fold into cooled lemon mixture.
Put into cooked pie crust.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: spicy cherry pie
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, flour, cinnamon and juice. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Add cherries and mix lightly.
Pour into bottom crust. Cover with top crust and crimp to seal.
Cut several slices in top.
Bake in 400° oven until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marinated chuck roast
directions: Mix oil and vinegar and pour in dish big enough to hold roast. Coat each side of roast with other ingredients.
Then piece roast with cooking fork several times on each side.
Place in oil and vinegar mixture and cover with aluminum foil.
Marinate in refrigerator for 4 to 8 hours, turning roast several times.
Cook on medium to low heat grill for 20 minutes.
Turn and cook 20 minutes more.
Slice thin to serve.

title: five step pot roast
directions: Brown roast; place in Dutch oven or crock-pot.
Place Pepsi, Lipton onion soup mix, soup with water and brown gravy mix in container.
Cook until done.
tags: cream of mushroom soup with water

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Mix gelatin, sugar, salt, marshmallows and lemon juice in boiling water.
Chill until thick.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until set.
Double recipe to fill round mold.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Blend butter and flour, then press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Press nuts into top of crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.

title: seven-up cake
directions: *Last ingredient to be added.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Blend flour and baking soda; add with pineapple juice to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts and crushed pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crustless egg custard pie
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar; add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into a lightly greased 10-inch Pyrex pie plate. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender; drain and smash. Add cheese, milk and butter.
Add eggs, salt and pepper.
You can add cream of mushroom soup, if you like.
Sprinkle stuffing on bottom of dish, then pour mixture on top.
Make 3 layers.
For top layer, sprinkle stuffing on top, melt some margarine and pour on top of stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well; store in airtight container. Use approximately 3 teaspoons per 8 ounce cup.

title: grape-nuts and oatmeal
directions: Microwave:
Mix all ingredients in a microwavable bowl.
Cook at High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole; bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve with hot biscuits.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: south seas pork tenderloin
directions: Trim fat from tenderloin.
Combine pork and next 6 ingredients in a ziploc bag.
Seal and marinate in the refrigerator 8 hours or overnight.
Prepare the grill, place pork on rack.
Grill 12 minutes, turning frequently and basting with reserved marinade. Grill pineapple and pork for 8 additional minutes, turning and basting.
Serve.

title: rice and beef porcupines
directions: Mix rice, beef, onion and seasoning; form into small balls. Fry in hot oil, turning frequently, until light brown on all sides.
Add tomato sauce and water; mix well.
Cover; simmer for about 45 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: coconut cake(real rich)
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed on box.
Take out of oven. Punch holes all over it while hot, with a fork.
Pour cream of coconut over cake.
After it cools, spread (room temperature) on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Coat a saucepan with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and next 2 ingredients; saute 3 minutes until tender.
Add water and next 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil; cook 2 minutes.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes. Add rice and simmer for 20 more minutes, or until rice is done and lentils are tender.
Stir well.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: Add gelatin and water; allow to soften.
Combine nonfat milk, evaporated skim milk, peanut butter and brown sugar in pan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with whisk.
Just before mixture comes to boil, remove from heat.
(If allowed to boil, mixture will separate and have a grainy texture.
This does not ruin taste but appearance.)
Add vanilla extract and gelatin; mix well.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into 8 custard cups and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add pineapple and stir in bread cubes.
Bake in a greased 1 1/4-quart casserole, uncovered, until golden.
Serve hot or cold.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well in a large bowl.
Let sit until room temperature. Roll into balls the size of large marbles.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350°
for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: nancy's new pie crust
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt, work in butter or shortening by hand.
Cut ice water in with fork.	Chill, roll out and bake. 375°

title: marbled cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Pour half batter evenly over prepared crust.
Stir melted chocolate into remaining batter.
Spoon over vanilla batter.
With table knife swirl through batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until set. Cool.
Cut in bars.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice into pan, then sprinkle onion soup mix over rice.
Mix mushroom soup with water and pour into pan.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with aluminum foil; seal.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: peach enchiladas
directions: Place a piece of fruit on wide end of each crescent roll-roll up. Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
May use other fruit or even canned or frozen fruit. Then mix remaining ingredients -pour over rolls.
Pour the Mountain Dew over this. Bake in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jan's tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directions ask.
Pour into a very large casserole dish.
Add tomatoes and Ro-Tel, then all other ingredients.
Sprinkle top with more Italian seasoning or parsley. Quick and delicious.

title: microwave cauliflower scramble
directions: Remove cauliflower pouches from boxes.
Place both pouches in oven.
Microwave at High (100%) until thawed, but not hot, 4 to 6 minutes.
If using oven without carousel, rearrange pouches once. Set aside.

title: steaks in irish mist
directions: Season steaks well with salt and pepper.
Heat pan and when hot, add butter.
When butter bubbles, add the steaks and cook 4 minutes (or longer if desired) on either side.
Remove to warm platter.
Add cream and liquor to juices in pan.
Stir and pour over steaks.
Serve immediately.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and beat.
Add cocoa, salt and flour; beat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 30 minutes.
Pour marshmallows over and place in oven for another 10 minutes.

title: low-cholesterol holiday nog
directions: Mix equal parts of Vernor's ginger ale and white grape juice. Chilled ingredients and an ice ring make it even better.

title: pear and raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease twelve 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch muffin-pan cups (1/3 cup); set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In a small bowl, lightly beat egg whites.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten flour.
Mix in cereal, pear and raisins.
Fill prepared muffin-pan cups about 2/3 full. Bake until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken soup, sour cream, poppy seed and 1 roll crushed Ritz crackers.
Put in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle 1 roll crumbled Ritz crackers on top; pour melted butter over the top for taste.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Take flour and cut in lard until well mixed.
Beat egg; add vinegar and salt.
Mix into flour and lard mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: pineapple lemon angel
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix together juice and enough water to make 3 cups.
Add sugar and bring to boil.
Pour over gelatin and dissolve.
Add orange and lemon juices.
Fold in whipped cream.
With forks, tear cake into small 1-inch pieces. Put 1/2 the cake lightly into 9 x 13 pan.
Spoon gelatin mixture over cake.
Repeat layers, do not pack.
Top should have irregular surface.
Chill for 24 hours.
Cut into squares and garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
Serves 18 to 24.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all together and chill at least 1 hour.
For creamed slaw, add 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: raw potato casserole
directions: Mix ground meat with tomato soup, salt, pepper and flour.
Mix well.
Form into balls the size of golf balls.
Melt butter in skillet and brown balls on all sides.

title: pink delight
directions: Bring egg yolks (beaten), milk and sugar to a boil and cool to thin custard.
Add jello, cool completely and whip.
Whip the cream; add crushed pineapple.
Beat egg whites and combine all ingredients.
Break angel food cake and line the bottom of a pan. Pour mixture on top of cake layer.
Repeat layers as before in pan.
Put some sour cream over top of mixture in pan about an hour before serving.

title: homemade sticky buns
directions: About 4 hours before serving or day ahead, in a large bowl, combine sugar, salt, yeast and 2 cups flour.
In 1-quart saucepan over low heat, heat 1 1/2 cups water and 1/2 cup margarine or butter until very warm (120° to 130°); margarine or butter does not need to melt completely.
With mixer at low speed, gradually beat liquid into dry ingredients just until blended.
Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Beat in egg and 1 cup flour to make a thick batter; continue beating 2 minutes, scraping bowl often.
With wooden spoon, stir in 2 1/4 cups flour to make a soft dough.

title: sausage spread
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add other ingredients.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut English muffins into fours.
Place on baking sheet and broil until hot and bubbling. Makes 24 pieces.

title: damson plum preserves
directions: Wash plums and cut from seeds.
Save seeds and wrap in cheesecloth; cook with plums.
This gives plums much more flavor. Combine all ingredients.
Cook on low heat until sugar is melted and then bring to rapid boil.
Reduce heat and cook slowly 45 to 50 minutes, or until jelled.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and put into an oblong baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine soups, sour cream, milk, onion, salt, pepper and dill weed. Stir until blended.
Add thawed hash brown potatoes, mixing until potatoes are completely coated.
Turn potato mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle evenly with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake 1 1/2 hours until browned and bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken noodle sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage, celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix with dry soup and half of water.
Mix with rice and mushrooms.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate graham cookies
directions: Section crackers into fourths and dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: corn flakes candy
directions: Mix corn flakes, Rice Krispies and peanuts together; set aside.
Cook Karo, sugar and cream until a soft ball forms, stirring constantly.
Pour over corn flakes mixture.
Mix well and put in a buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix pineapple with flour and sugar.
Pour in a baking dish. Melt oleo.
To this add cubed bread.
After mixing bread with melted oleo, put on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake 20 minutes (or until browned and bubbly) at 400°.
Serve warm.
Delicious with ham.

title: beef ball
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cheese.
Add all other ingredients, except meat and onions.
Work into a paste, using mixer.
Add meat and onions.
Cover with tinfoil and chill for 2 hours.
Roll in nuts.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning (making according to package instructions).
Layer cream cheese in 9 x 9-inch pan, put ground beef on top, then layer olives, scallions and Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with nachos.
Serve hot.

title: daddy's homemade hot chocolate
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in pan.
Combine can of evaporated milk and 3 cans of water.
Heat and serve.

title: fried clams
directions: Beat egg in a small bowl and add milk.
In a separate bowl, mix flour with salt, pepper and paprika.
Put cracker meat in another bowl.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(skillet)
directions: This one may be a little strange to you, but is a classic in its own right.
The difference between this one and the one you usually find in the cookbook, is that this one uses a skillet for a baking pan.

title: beef with peppers
directions: Broil peppers until charred on all sides.
Remove and place them in paper bag (to steam) for 10 minutes; remove skins and seeds.
Slice peppers into thin strips.
Set aside.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of the sugar in heavy 8-inch skillet, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted and golden brown.
Remove from heat; stir in boiling water slowly.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar lumps are dissolved.
Add enough water to syrup, if necessary, to measure 1/2 cup; cool.

title: walnut surprise cookies
directions: Stir together.
Spread in a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Add tomato sauce, Cheddar cheese, drained corn and optional black olives to beef mixture.
Place crescents in pie pan; beat one egg and put over crescents.
Then put 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese over crescents and the one egg.
Put beef mixture over the crescents and put cheese on top.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, frost and cut.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until it just starts to boil; let cool.
Cut biscuits in half or quarters and roll into balls. Combine 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in a Baggie and shake ball in mixture.
Put in greased Bundt pan; use half of the biscuits. Pour 1/2 of the syrup over the balls and repeat.
(Add nuts, if desired.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Let stand in pan a few minutes after removing from oven, then invert onto a large plate.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate bit drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: dehart chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 3 to 4 hours or until thick.

title: peanut butter popcorn balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, light corn syrup and sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over popcorn and form into balls.

title: german sweet chocolate cake frosting
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients until thick. Add the last 3 after cooling the sauce. Spread on layer cake or loaf cake.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix together salmon, 3 cups mashed potatoes, egg and Mrs. Dash. Form into patties about the size of hamburger patties.
Coat each patty with flour and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Fry in oil over medium temperature until nicely browned on both sides.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Clean carrots.
Cut in strips about 1/4-inch wide.
Cook in salted water until almost tender.
Drain and reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Put carrots in casserole.

title: ambrosia eggnog candy
directions: Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In prepared pan, combine sugar, eggnog and syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to boiling.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°) without stirring.
Immediately remove from heat; cool to lukewarm (110°) without stirring.
Add butter and vanilla; beat vigorously until very thick and candy just starts to lose its gloss, about 8 minutes.
Quickly stir in cherries and coconut. Pour into buttered 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds candy.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Roll on a floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat together.
Pour in can and fill to fill line with homogenized milk.

title: rotel taco dip
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
When light in color, drain off fluid. In crock-pot or slow cooker, blend in other ingredients with meat. Heat until cheese melts on high, then turn to low and serve hot with taco shells.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Shape into small balls. Brown in 1/2 cup cooking oil.
when brown, pour off oil.
Top each ball with catsup.
Add vegetables.
Cover with water.
Cook in a covered container over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
I like to use an electric frying pan.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber sauce for fish
directions: Use cucumbers which have not been wax coated.
Chop coarsely. Leave in colander about 30 minutes to drain.
Squeeze out moisture before combining with remaining ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator a few hours for flavors to blend.
Makes 1 1/2 cups, about 13 calories per tablespoon.

title: eggs supreme
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs; add milk, onion, salt, mustard and pepper.
Put croutons in pan first, then cheese and mushrooms and add eggs last.
Sprinkle with ham or bacon pieces. Put foil on top and refrigerate if doing ahead of time.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: low-fat chocolate eclair
directions: Place one layer of graham crackers in bottom of pan. Mix pudding and milk for 2 minutes. Add Cool Whip to pudding mixture. Pour 1/2 of mixture over crackers. Add another layer of crackers. Spread chocolate frosting over top layer of crackers. Chill.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix the milk, oil, egg whites and bananas together.
Mix well.
Add this mixture to the dry ingredients.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour the batter into the muffin cups, filling each 3/4 full.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 17 minutes.

title: chinese salad
directions: Take a large bowl and place torn lettuce (dried) in bottom. Place peas to cover lettuce.
Then place sliced onions to cover peas.
Then place water chestnuts to cover onions.
Continue layers until bowl is filled.
Spread a thick layer of mayonnaise on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Place in refrigerator for 5 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: old fashioned nut cake
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, sugar and flavor.
Add margarine.
Beat together.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and stir into eggs. Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until center springs back at light touch. Cool for 10 minutes.
Loosen edges with knife.
Turn out into racks and let cool completely.

title: gazpacho
directions: Chop vegetables and place in blender with remaining ingredients. Blend until pureed. Serve as it comes from blender or strain, if you wish. Garnish with sliced cucumbers, tomato wedges and chopped green pepper. Serve cold. Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pickled asparagus
directions: Heat to simmer water, vinegar, salt and pickling spice.
Pack asparagus in quart jars with 1 clove of garlic, fresh dill
and the spices.
Pour hot solution over.
Seal and process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Follow directions on Dream Whip and make 1 envelope.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Add powdered sugar.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Top with can of cherry pie filling.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Mix these ingredients together and put in hamburg.
Simmer 20 minutes and serve your favorite way.

title: easy vanilla ice cream
directions: In large bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Freeze according to instructions. Freeze leftovers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together with mixer. Pour into casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients with fork until crumbles and put on top of casserole. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herbed shrimp and pasta
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and set aside; keep warm. Melt butter in a heavy skillet over medium-high heat; add shrimp and garlic. Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly; remove shrimp and set aside, reserving garlic and butter in skillet. Add half and half to skillet; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low and simmer about 15 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally. Add shrimp, parsley and seasonings; stir until blended. Serve over angel hair pasta with steamed or sauteed red, green and yellow pepper strips.

title: no fail chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients and mix until the mixture thickens.
Stir slowly while cooking.
Beat in electric mixer until smooth, making a very creamy filling.
Cool and pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Start the dip with layer of beans, add the sour cream over beans, spread avocados over sour cream and continue layering until finished.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: marzetta
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine until golden brown. Add meat and stir until all is brown. Add tomato puree/sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles, drain and rinse.
Layer noodles, then cheese and then meat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (be sure heated all the way through).

title: corn and tomato soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except milk; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in milk and heat through.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together all the ingredients except vanilla and peanut butter.
Cook over medium heat until a small amount dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and stir in peanut butter.
Beat with spoon until smooth and glossy and begins to thicken.
Pour into lightly buttered dish until cool.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all together.
Pat out dough on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beulah's chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg in 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in flour mixture.
In skillet, brown chicken in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon in water, add with remaining lemon juice to skillet. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Garnish as desired.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Line a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with wax paper.
Set aside.
Combine cranberries, 1 cup sugar and water in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, or until cranberry skins pop. Drain and set aside.
Beat shortening at medium speed until creamy, gradually adding remaining 2/3 cup sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to shortening mixture, alternating with banana, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix after each addition.
Fold in reserved cranberries and walnuts.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Remove wax paper and let cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: jumbles jubilee cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar, sugar and eggs; stir in sour cream, vanilla, flour and salt.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mizza pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and put in deep pie dish.
Cover with optional items. Bake at 370° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: white rolled cookies
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together in a bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl, cut shortening into flour, baking soda and powder. Mix by hand together.
When mixed, add to beaten sugar and eggs. Knead until smooth.
Chill for several hours.
When ready to make cookies, roll quite thin on lightly floured board.
Cut out cookies with cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar or decorate.
Bake in 350° oven until creamy color and very crisp, approximately 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Let cheese and butter get to room temperature. With mixer, cream the cheese and butter together.
Add other ingredients and mix until well blended.
Great on pineapple cake.

title: chicken with almonds
directions: Mix the sliced chicken with the salt, wine and cornstarch; marinate for 10 minutes.
Place the almonds in a cold wok; stir over medium heat until the almonds begin to toast.
Remove them from the wok and set aside.
Heat the wok.
Add the peanut oil; stir in the chicken, reserving any marinade.
When chicken begins to turn white, stir in the onion.
Stir a few times.
Stir in the snow peas, stock and reserved marinade.
Stir 2 minutes until the onion is translucent and soft.
Stir in about 3/4 cup of the almonds.
Serve immediately, sprinkled with the remaining almonds. Serve over rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: mandarin salad oriental
directions: Remove packet of seasoning from Ramen noodles and mix with sugar, oil, salt, pepper, and hot sauce.
Set aside.
Crumble noodles and bake with almonds at 350° for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven and cool.
Toss together lettuce and celery.
Add baked noodles, almonds, liquid mixture and mandarin oranges.
Serve immediately.

title: family meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients into a loaf pan (8 x 4 x 2-inch shallow pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let meat loaf stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle.
Cover and bring to low boil on high heat.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook very slowly, covered, for about an hour.
For a chunkier version, cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
For low-fat, season with margarine or lean meat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs and margarine. Place mixture in buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake until brown.
Beat together the cream cheese, powder sugar and 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Put on cooled crust.
Beat the pudding and milk together.
Spread on cream cheese mixture, then put the other half of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Cut up head of lettuce.
Add chopped onion, pepper and celery. Mix in peas (uncooked) and mayonnaise with lettuce, etc.
Put in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, add cup of grated cheese on top.
Make night before or a.m. before serving.

title: egg nog and sweet potato casserole
directions: Slice enough sweet potatoes to cover 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Slice 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Stir good and pour over the layer of potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Press around dish good so potatoes will cook.
When cooked, remove foil and cook until syrup is thick as you like. Don't let syrup get too thick.
Cook in oven at 325° to 350°.

title: cool whip fruit salad
directions: Mix together well, chill and serve.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into pieces or strips; brown meat and salt.
Push meat to one side of pan, add onion, cook and stir until tender, stir in broth, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add green peppers.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch in 1/4 cup water, gradually stir into meat mixture stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cover for 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: aunt ruth's casserole
directions: Cook noodles; set aside.
Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper, then drain.
Mix with corn, noodles and green beans or peas.
Cut up cheese in chunks; put 3/4 of it in.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover for last 10 minutes. Add remaining cheese on top.

title: easy icing
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Mix until creamy.
Takes a long time to mix with hand mixer.
Must be refrigerated.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening with both cups of sugar.
Add eggs.
Cream in peanut butter and vanilla.
Combine all dry ingredients and work with hands into the creamed mixture.
Form desired size balls and press with a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 16 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture; blend well. Add chocolate and nuts. Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from sheet immediately. Place on cooling rack. Enjoy!

title: spoon rolls
directions: Combine water and yeast.
Melt margarine and combine with sugar.
Add flour and yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remainder of dough will refrigerate for several days.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower as directed on packages (I cook them together).
Drain.
Add 1 can of celery soup.
Spread these ingredients in a baking dish; cover with cheese slices.
Top with French onion rings.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot buns
directions: Grind together the Spam, onion and green pepper.
Add the tomato paste.
Melt in saucepan the butter and cheese.
Combine with meat mixture.
Spread on hamburger buns and wrap individually in aluminum foil.
Heat in oven 10 minutes at 425°.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve both jellos in hot water, then add cold water.
Put in refrigerator and let set until it starts to jell good.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Return to refrigerator and let chill good. Cover with small marshmallows.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan and cook slightly over low heat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into dish and chill.
If you want to make a mold, pour into mold that has been rubbed with salad oil and chill overnight.
To help in removing from mold, place in warm water.

title: glazed cheesecake puffs
directions: Place vanilla wafers in paper-lined muffin cups.
Cream sugar, cream cheese, eggs and vanilla in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Fill prepared muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Spread pie filling on cooled cheesecakes.
Chill until serving time.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into patties and fry in shortening until brown.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce at least 30 minutes; drain and roll each in sugar.
Wrap each water chestnut with a piece of bacon, securing with a toothpick.
Arrange on cake rack in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep hot on warming tray. Yields about 16.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp and sugar.
Then add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to pulp mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Melt butter in
a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add to mixture but leave enough to grease pan well.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat until it spins a thread.
While this mixture is cooking, put coconut and butter into a mixing bowl.
When sugar mixture spins a thread, pour over the coconut and butter.
Beat for a few minutes.
Pour into a buttered platter.
Cool.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: island style chicken
directions: Drain pineapple.
In skillet, brown chicken in shortening. Pour off fat.
Add syrup, broth, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover; cook over low heat for 40 minutes.
Add green pepper and pineapple; cook 5 minutes more, or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Combine cornstarch and gradually stir into sauce. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: pepperoni breadsticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix, cold water and pepperoni until dough forms.
Beat 20 strokes.
Turn dough onto surface dusted with baking mix; gently roll to coat and knead 5 times.

title: aunt ethel's chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over rice.
Put onion soup on top.
Put chicken on top. Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Uncover to brown chicken.

title: realemon touchdown
directions: In a pitcher, combine all ingredients except ice. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Serve over ice.
Makes 5 cups.
Enjoy.

title: rangoon
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Fill wonton with approximately 1 teaspoon of mixture.
Deep fry approximately 6 seconds.
Serve with orange marmalade.

title: family favorite cabbage rolls
directions: Steam cabbage until tender.
Combine rice, water and salt; cook for 20 minutes.
Mix together cooked rice, beef, onion, 1 1/2 teaspoons Season-All, pepper and basil leaves.
Place 1/3 cup of meat mixture in each cabbage leaf.
Roll and tuck in ends.
Fasten with a toothpick.
Place rolls in frying pan.
Cover with tomatoes and juice; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove rolls.

title: bill's monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix the first sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Roll each biscuit piece in sugar mixture. Pile into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Set aside. Melt the butter in a saucepan with the sugar and cinnamon.
When sugar melts, pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in the center. In another bowl, mix oil, eggs, water and pumpkin, then pour into dry ingredients and blend well.
Add nuts and raisins.

title: cherry nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream again.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in cherries, coconut and pecans. Spoon batter into greased and floured 10 x 4-inch tube cake pan. Bake in 350° gas oven 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool on rack.
Yield: 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: all american turkey burgers
directions: Preheat charcoal grill for direct heat cooking.

title: easy tarts
directions: Drop dough by spoonfuls into 36 tart cups.
Bake as directed on package.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Set aside.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt; dip in salad dressing and roll in corn flake crumbs.
Place skin side up in foil lined baking dish. Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill and serve.

title: chocolate elcair pudding
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with whole graham crackers, cutting with knife to sit.
Mix French vanilla pudding with 3 cups milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour on top of crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Melt chocolate with margarine and add 3 tablespoons milk.
When melted, add confectioners sugar and beat until smooth.
Very quickly.
Pour on top of assembly.
If possible, let set overnight and the graham crackers will soften and taste just like a pate a chow eclair case.

title: grandma cole's creamed oysters
directions: Make white sauce with cream, butter and flour.
Shell eggs. Chop yolks fine; add mustard, lemon juice and a small pat of butter.
Chop egg whites fine and mix into white sauce.
Add yolk mixture to white sauce.
Season with salt, onion salt and Old Bay seasoning.
Cook oysters separately until edges begin to curl. Add only oysters to white sauce.
Save liquid; add a little to sauce.
Heat very slowly before serving.
Serve over sliced turkey, stuffing or plain.

title: keer krispy bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice as thin as possible. Slice onions as thin as possible. Combine with cucumbers and salt. Let stand 3 hours and drain. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in a large kettle and bring to a boil. Add drained cucumbers and onions. Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Pack hot into jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Yields 14 pints.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and add milk and shortening. Pour into ungreased pan.
Mix brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over cake.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese topped pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Beat eggs in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until thick.
Stir in flour, pineapple, pecans, baking soda and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Pour into pan and bake until tester inserted in center comes out clean. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cake cool in pan on rack.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease large pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until inserted knife comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and garnish with tomato slices and bacon strips if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: feather light rolls
directions: Scald milk and add oleo.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add sugar.
In a bowl, beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and then add milk and yeast.
Add flour and mix to soft dough.
Let raise overnight. Next morning, roll out and cut into rolls.
Place in pan and let raise 5 to 6 more hours and bake.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening,
Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Add to buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Roll out thin, fold over and roll again.
Cut like biscuits.
Saturate with butter.
May be baked immediately or will keep in refrigerator in bulk. Cook as you would biscuits.
This will keep for several days.
You do not have to let rise before baking. Bake at 375°.

title: pineapple cheese roll
directions: In medium bowl with fork, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, the green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil.
Refrigerate until well chilled.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine onion, butter, soup, mushrooms, almonds, water chestnuts, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Gently fold in peas.
Place half this mixture in buttered casserole dish.
Top with 1 sliced egg.
Add remaining pea mixture.
Top with remaining sliced egg.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cook meat in oil over low heat until tender, but not browned. Add onions, mushrooms, celery, green onions and bamboo shoots. Cover and cook five minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add and dissolve bouillon cube in the hot water.
Add and combine remaining ingredients with meat.
Cook for 15 minutes longer. Serve with rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Place chicken or turkey in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Drain mushrooms; reserve liquid.
Top chicken with mushrooms and stuffing.
Combine mushroom liquid, 10 3/4 ounce can cream of chicken soup and 1/2 cup water.
Pour over stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pizza quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate with pastry, or use frozen pie shells.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Layer tomatoes, chiles, onion, pepperoni and cheeses.
Beat eggs until foamy; stir in half and half.
Add garlic, oregano and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve.

title: black cherry jello dish
directions: Drain the two cans of cherries. Place cherries in a bowl. Put the juice and the sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pull from heat and add the almond extract. Pour the cherry juice mixture over the cherries and cover with film. Refrigerate overnight in refrigerator.

title: easy chicken 'n rice
directions: Boil chicken in salt water until tender.
Debone and add back to broth; add soups, dry cream of chicken, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Let simmer for a few minutes or as long as you wish.
Add rice about 5 minutes before serving.
It needs to be real soupy when mixed.
After a few minutes it will become stiffer.

title: cranberry wine punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice
and
lemon peel and bring to a boil. Simmer 15 minutes, then add remaining ingredients.

title: sweet, fresh broccoli salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients in bowl.

title: farm fry
directions: Fry bacon until brittle, then chop into pieces.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of grease.
Combine potatoes, bacon, onion, salt and pepper; brown lightly.
Add eggs, then mix.
Top off with cheese.

title: kentucky dream cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine with sugar and egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 or 3 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) layers at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: saturday morning oatmeal waffles
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
In small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour batter onto waffle iron.
Bake until steaming stops.
Makes 12 waffles, 4 squares each.

title: any fruit cobbler
directions: Pour melted butter or margarine into bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan. In mixing bowl combine flour, sugar and milk.
Mix together and pour over margarine.
Place fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: eva's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and 1/2 cup water; set aside to rise before mixing all together.
Mix all together and put in buttered bowl.
Let rise.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Dip in melted margarine.
Fold over and place in pan.
Place warm cloth over rolls and let rise.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until done. Brush with melted margarine.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put applesauce in oblong 9 x 12-inch baking dish that has been generously greased with butter.
Combine oatmeal, vanilla wafers (crushed) and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Melt butter and add to oatmeal mixture.
Blend well and spread evenly over the applesauce.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Serve hot.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix.
Put in refrigerator for at least 12 hours.

title: quick cheese cake
directions: Unroll one package of crescent rolls and place in bottom of pan.
Mix together first 4 ingredients and spread on top of rolls. Unroll second package of crescent rolls and place on top of cheese mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.

title: orange cranberry bread
directions: Chop cranberries until coarse.
Chop pecans coarsely; reserve. In a bowl, cream sugar, butter and orange rind until smooth.
In another bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Mix the orange juice and egg together until well blended. Stir the flour mixture into the sugar mixture until blended.
Add the orange juice and egg.
Stir until blended but do not overmix. It will be rather stiff.
Add the cranberries and pecans.
Turn into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Layer cauliflower, tuna and mushrooms in a 1-quart casserole. Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over layers.
Microwave on High (100%) for 6 to 8 minutes or until heated through.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Melt butter. Add the confectioners sugar, peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs and mix well.
Melt the chocolate chips. Spread on top. Cool and cut in squares.

title: reese peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine with peanut butter; add confectioners sugar. Mix well and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt Hershey bars and spread on top.
Cool in refrigerator until set. Cut into bars.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Combine the remaining ingredients and beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating well.
Form 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven about 10 minutes.
Makes 48.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and cream cheese; gradually add sugar.
Beat well at medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring just until blended.
Stir in vanilla and coconut flavorings until blended.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove on wire rack and let cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Flour nuts and raisins.
Pour water over 2 cups cereal and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Fold in flour, salt, soda and cereal and mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add raisins, nuts and chopped apples.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes in mini muffin tins or 20 minutes in regular muffin tins.
Store in refrigerator and do not stir when ready to use.
Keep 4 to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: mushroom-cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Press dough in bottom of pan with floured hands.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Mix all batter ingredients together including liquids.
Beat well.
Then add fruit and nuts.
Stir in.
Pour into 1 tube pan, angel food type, that has been greased well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool in pan.

title: candy cookie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add instant oatmeal and vanilla.

title: cantonese beef in oyster sauce
directions: Cut beef into thin slices about 1 1/2 inches across.
In a medium bowl, combine sliced beef, a pinch of salt, pepper, sugar, soy sauce, wine or sherry, cornstarch and egg.
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut each Chinese cabbage leaf into 2 or 3 pieces. Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add 2 tablespoons oil.
When oil smokes, add cabbage pieces.
Stir-fry 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until leaves become limp.
Quickly remove with a slotted spoon; place cabbage in a serving dish.

title: grandma's christmas roll out cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out.
Bake at 400° approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: thanksgiving cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add apples, butterscotch chips,
nuts and vanilla. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for
to
minutes. While cake is warm, prepare topping.

title: pasta and vegetables
directions: Combine cheeses, egg whites, thyme, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Set aside.
Steam broccoli, onions, carrots and celery until broccoli is crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Add pasta and oil to large pot of boiling water and cook until pasta is just tender, but still firm to bite, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Return to pot.
Add steamed vegetables and toss. Add cheese mixture and toss.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Spoon tomatoes in center of pasta.
Garnish edges with parsley.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Then add the next 3.
Put in lightly greased cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pecan nuts (chopped) on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and put in punch bowl.
Makes 40 cups.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil, ranch mix, dill in bowl. Put into shaker bag. Add crackers. shake to coat well. Enjoy!

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.

title: alo-balo polo
directions: Wash the rice and soak in salt water for about 2 hours. Combine the cherries and sugar in a 2 or 3-quart pan and bring to a boil over high heat while stirring gently.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in bacon grease.
Add vinegar along with the rest. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes, until sauce thickens.
Diced pepper may be added.
Good for barbecue meat.

title: orange bread
directions: Cook cut peel in water until peel is tender, about 20 minutes. Add the sugar and cook 30 minutes longer with a very low heat. Let cool.
Add milk, egg, fat and sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well and turn into two well-greased bread pans.
Let stand 25 minutes, then bake 1 hour at 375°.
Brush top with soft butter when removed from oven.

title: chocko and terre's cancun chicken
directions: Coat chicken breasts with egg and bread crumbs; fry in canola oil.
Place breaded and fried chicken breasts in ovenproof pan. Saute onions in frypan until translucent.
Cover chicken breasts with onions.
Grate Mozzarella cheese and cover onions with cheese.
Place pan in oven until cheese is melted to your liking, then serve.

title: vegetable pita melt
directions: Blanch broccoli and cauliflower.
In a small mixing bowl combine all ingredients except pita and cheese, mixing well until thoroughly coated.
Cut pita in half crosswise, making 2 halves. Open each half to form a pocket.
Fill each pita half with half of the vegetable mixture and then with 1/2 ounce cheese.
Set pita halves on paper plate and microwave on High for 40 seconds.
Makes 1 serving.
May be increased.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Tenderize the chops, they should not be very thin.
Salt and pepper from both sides.
