Dredge chops in flour, shake off excess of flour.
Over medium heat in frying pan heat about 4 Tbsp. oil. Try the chops from both sides, until tender.
Remove the chops from pan, keep in warm place until you prepare the sauce.
To prepare the sauce add a little bit of water, about 1/3 cup, to pan juices, scrape the brown bits from bottom.
Add Hungarian paprika and mustard, stirring constantly.
As soon as it starts to boil, slowly add whipping cream, reduce the heat and add lemon juice. Stir constantly.
Return meat to pan and cook about 2 to 4 minutes longer.
Serve over mashed potatoes with slices of lemon and decorate with fresh parsley.

title: spinach squares
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in beaten eggs, milk and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until moistened.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips while partially frozen.
In skillet, brown meat and cook onion in butter until onion is tender.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Add gravy. Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until the meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
If necessary, add a little water.

title: sourdough cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix Start and oil.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt; add to starter and oil.
On a floured board, roll the mixture into a rectangular shape.
Spread on butter; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll (jelly roll fashion).
Slice about 1-inch thick. Let rise for 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: potted apples for fried pies
directions: Place ingredients in heavy large skillet.
Cook slowly on medium-high heat for 2 to 3 hours until mixture is thick.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Put mixture in hot jars, seal and process in hot water bath for 5 minutes, or put in heavy freezer Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk together in pan.
Let come to full boil, then boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from burner.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; stir until completely blended, then beat until it starts to thicken.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: chicken dinner in a pot
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place chicken breasts in large heavy ovenware pot.
Peel potatoes, sliced 1/2-inch thick, and place on top of chicken.
Peel and quarter the onion lengthwise and cut into 2-inch lengths.
Cut ends off green beans or separate frozen beans. Place in pot with onion and carrots.
Sprinkle contents of pot with parsley.
Season.
Bake 2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add ingredients and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are done.

title: shrimp marinara
directions: Heat the oil and cook shrimp and garlic briefly for about 3 minutes, just until shrimp turns pink.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 2 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: old fashioned lemon sauce
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until just boiling.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Cut oleo into flour; add pecans and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes and cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce, Accent and dried chopped beef in bowl.
Form ball.
Put pecans on wax paper and roll cheese ball back and forth until completely covered. Chill and serve with your choice of crackers.

title: microwave apple bread pudding
directions: Mix together pudding mix and milk in a 2-quart micro bowl. Cook on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in apples, spices and vanilla. Cook 2 minutes longer.
Stir in bread cubes.
Cook 1 to 2 1/2 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix margarine with crackers.
Make 2 layers in a greased Pyrex dish (8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch) of asparagus, soup, nuts, cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, peanut butter, water and eggs.
By hand, stir with spoon until dough is formed.
Stir in peanut butter chips.

title: italian-style meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine the meat, egg, bread crumbs, onion, seasonings and 1/2 can pizza sauce. Mix well. Form into a large round loaf and place in a 3-quart round casserole.
Pour the remaining pizza sauce over the meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Top with the sliced cheese and bake 5 more minutes. Remove from the oven and let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: evelyn's chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, water and undiluted soup together.
Stir in chicken, onion, chestnuts, pepper, rice and salt.
Carefully add sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Place all in a greased casserole.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve baking soda in the buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add salt, vanilla and lemon extract.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: stuffed pepper surprise
directions: Blanch pepper halves in boiling water for 2 minutes or until barely tender.
Drain peppers.
Lay cut side down on paper towel.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until barely tender. Drain.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients to soup mixture.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Mix cream ingredients together.
Layer cheese between.
Heat in smooth crock-pot until cheese is melted and dip is hot.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Note:
Cubed eggplant can also be added to the vegetables.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Beat well until blended.
Add butter to milk and bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add egg mixture and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Place on paper towels to drain.
In bacon grease, saute the green onions, celery and Spam.
When crisp-tender, add the cooked rice, scrambled eggs and crumbled bacon.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: stack cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add sorghum and eggs, beating after each addition. Sift flour and other dry ingredients together. Add flour and milk alternately to batter. Roll out on a flour-covered surface. (Makes 10 to 12 layers.) Bake in iron skillets at 350°.

title: cauliflower salad bowl
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and mixture thoroughly.
Chill prior to serving.

title: spud bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugars in bowl.
Beat in everything but eggs, vanilla and potatoes.
Fold in eggs, vanilla and potatoes with spatula.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut and remove from pan while still warm.
Makes 32 (2-inch) square bars.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in a casserole.
Add crushed Ritz crackers on top with 1 stick of butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours to marinate.
This recipe can be varied with different combinations of vegetables.
Any fresh vegetable could be added.

title: chicken rice casserole(from leftovers)
directions: Mix together and place in greased or sprayed casserole. Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes to warm thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: purple passion
directions: Mix cherry juice with softened cream cheese and pineapple tidbits, marshmallows and nuts. Mix with one tub of Cool Whip. Chill 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Flatten cookies on pan, cook according to package directions. Let cookies cool.
Mix cream cheese and vanilla until smooth. Spread over cookies.
Layer fruit as desired.
Refrigerate.

title: frog bellies
directions: Make into dough. Roll out and cut into squares, about 2-inches. Drop into hot deep cooking oil and cook until brown. Serve with maple syrup and butter.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar; add eggs (beat eggs separately and add to cocoa and sugar).
Cream.
Add melted butter to batter.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into one deep dish uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes, until done.

title: beer and sauerkraut fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift cocoa, flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with beer, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in sauerkraut, raisins and/or nuts (optional). Turn into two 8 or 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and frost as desired.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium bowl with the lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
In a large shallow platter, spread bean dip, then top with avocado mixture and sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese. Serve at room temperature or chilled with lots of chips.

title: ed's simple marmalade
directions: Pour 2 cups sugar in a large pot.
Add water; watch, you need to make a heavy syrup.
Simmer until color starts to darken.
In a food processor shred the oranges.
Put cinnamon and oranges into heavy syrup and stir.
Cook until done.
Let cool and then refrigerate.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake crusts for 5 minutes.
Brown sausage.
Add the sausage and cheese to the crusts.
Mix the remaining ingredients and divide evenly between the 2 pans.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Combine chicken, onion, green chilies, milk and soups.
Set aside.
Pour margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan and coat bottom. Layer bottom of pan with flour tortilla quarters, chicken mixture and cheese. Repeat, ending with cheese on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on package and pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, oleo and confectioners sugar until real creamy.
Drop by tablespoon all over cake; it will cover cake.
Do not smooth out.
Put foil under pan in case it spills over.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt leila's 1-2-3-4 plain cake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, milk and flour.
Will completely fill 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 325°. Takes about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick light rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, let rise.
Then bake at 425° until brown.

title: coffee cake muffins
directions: Put flour, baking powder, sugar, egg and salt in a large bowl. Stir together well.
Mix in milk and vanilla.
Stir to moisten. Spoon part of batter into greased muffin tins 1/3 full.
Sprinkle spice mix over top.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: Cook noodles, drain and set aside.
In a skillet, combine meat, pepper, onion and garlic and cook until meat is done.
Drain and add all remaining ingredients except egg and cheeses.
Bring meat sauce to a boil and reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 -25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine eggs and cheeses.
To assemble, stir pasta into meat sauce.
Place 1/2 in a 1 quart buttered baking dish and spread cheese mixture evenly over top. Top with remaining pasta and bake at 350 degrees for 30 -35 minutes.

title: asparagus delight
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving 1 cup liquid; set aside.

title: devil's food pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Mix in all ingredients.
Blend together or beat ingredients until moistened. Pour in batter and bake
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.
Invert cake on plate or paper towels and cool.
Then frost with your favorite icing.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in the 3 cups water in a covered pot until tender.
Do not drain.
Mash some of the potatoes, then add milk, bouillon cubes and butter.
Mix sour cream and flour until smooth, then add to soup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and cubes dissolve.
Season with salt and pepper.
Last, add shredded carrots.

title: chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add the sugar, eggs, cocoa and vanilla.
Combine the flour and baking powder.
Stir into the chocolate mixture. Toast the nuts by spreading in a single layer in a shallow pan. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: jo ann foster's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Have meat ground together.
Soak bread crumbs in ketchup and water.
Season with pepper only.
Combine with meat, then add beaten eggs.
Shape
in loaf and bake in moderate oven for about 1 3/4 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: grandma addie's plain cake for little don
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix with mixer (2 minutes on high) or by hand (300 strokes). Will make 2 layers or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve plain or with your favorite icing.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Bake in greased loaf pan for about 1 hour at 350° oven.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine first three ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until coffee and sugar are dissolved.
Let cool.
Add in vodka and the vanilla bean, cut in half.
Pour mixture into a bottle and close top.
(Mrs. Butterworth's syrup bottles work well.)
Place in dark place for 3 weeks, shaking bottle every other day.
Make at Thanksgiving to be ready for the Christmas season!

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil water in a large pot and add oil and noodles.
Cook until al dente (not mushy).
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Toss with 1/2 cup Red Wine Basil Vinaigarette.
Boil beans 5 to 8 minutes or just tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Place pasta in a large bowl.
Cover with tomatoes, green beans, olives, 1 1/2 cups basil and parsley.
Pour vinaigarette over salad and top with cheese.
Toss and serve.

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250° and combine.
Pour melted butter into shallow baking pan.
Stir Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Add Chex's and Planters dry roasted peanuts.
Mix until all are coated with sauce.
Heat in 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towel.
Pour into bowl; it's ready to serve.

title: carrot and pineapple salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and dissolve.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar and salt.
Mix well and add pineapple, carrots and pecans.
Mix well and place in refrigerator to congeal.
Serve in squares on lettuce leaves. Top with a little mayonnaise.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beet juice; add sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and allspice. Cook until thick.
Add butter; pour over beets.
Let set 30 minutes before serving.
Heat again.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat the egg whites until stiff, adding 2 tablespoons of sugar and chocolate chips.
Combine all ingredients together.
Spread in a pan, 9 x 9-inch, and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let it cool off before icing, if desired.

title: cherry pie cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add vanilla, then flour.
Save back 1 cup of batter.
Pour rest of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread pie filling over batter, then the cup of batter over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk and then chocolate pieces.
Cook and stir over medium high heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir exactly 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir a moderate amount of hot mixture into yolks; immediately return to hot mixture.
Cook exactly 2 minutes more stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour into cooled baked pastry shell*.
Spread meringue atop pie and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: rover's rewards
directions: Preheat
oven to 325°.	In large bowl, pour
hot
water over margarine.	Stir in powdered milk, salt, sugar
and
egg. Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition. Knead 3 to 4 minutes, adding more flour if necessary to make a very stiff dough.
Pat or roll to 1/2-inch thickness
and
cut out
with
dog (or other) biscuit cutter.
Place	on
greased baking sheet and bake for 50 minutes.
Allow to cool
and
dry out until hard. Makes 60 biscuits.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until blended. Stir in milk and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted 1 inch from edge of pie comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Spread cheese on top. Bake 10 minutes more before serving.

title: chocolate toffee bark
directions: Line a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Place saltines in a single layer (salt side up).
In saucepan, boil butter, sugar and vanilla for 3 minutes until bubbly and syrupy.
Pour over crackers.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Remove and pour chocolate chips over crackers.
Let sit 2 minutes, then spread chocolate evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until cold, then break up into squares.

title: tailgate potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients (except corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter) together in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with melted butter and corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients except for cheese and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Pour melted butter over bread crumbs. Mix thoroughly. Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cut cheese slices into triangles. Alternately place layers of zucchini, onion, tomatoes, green pepper, cheese and bread crumbs in casserole. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and top with bread crumbs. Cover and bake in 350° oven for an hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: crazy cookies(microwave recipe)
directions: Place butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High (100%) for 45 seconds to 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs until well blended.
Press evenly in bottom of dish.
Microwave on High (100%) for 2 to 3 minutes or until set. Turn dish a half turn halfway through cooking.
Layer each of the remaining ingredients in order listed.
Microwave on Medium (50%) for 6 to 8 minutes or until bubbly.
Allow to stand on a solid surface until completely cooled.
Cut into bars.
Recipe yield:
1 dozen bars.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Mix all ingredients together; stir in the noodles.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.

title: yeast-raised irish soda bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour. In large bowl, mix remaining flour, undissolved yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat water, buttermilk and butter until hot to touch, 125° to 130°.
Stir into dry mixture. Mix raisins and enough reserved flour to make soft dough. Cover bowl; let rest 10 minutes.

Knead 10 times on lightly floured surface. Form 5 to 6 inch diameter ball. Place on greased baking sheet. Cover; let rise in warm, draft-free place until doubled in size, about 1 hour. Sprinkle dough lightly with 1 tablespoon flour.
With sharp knife, make 1/8 inch deep cross in top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Remove from baking sheet and cool on wire rack.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken slowly with onion and celery.
Drain and discard onion and celery used in cooking chicken.
Cut up chicken and sprinkle lemon juice over it.
Add celery, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and almonds.
Mix well.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans; set aside.
Pour half of batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of sugar mixture over batter.
Repeat procedure.
Gently swirl batter with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until slightly tender.
Drain; let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight.
Will keep indefinitely in the refrigerator.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into measuring cup.
Add enough water for 1 cup of liquid.
Bring to a boil.
When boiling, stir in the jello.
Add cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Combine the pineapple and cranberry sauce; stir into the gelatin.
Pour mixture into pan and chill until firm.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Mix and place in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and cut into chunks.
Combine whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Add fruit and nuts.
Freeze until very firm.

title: mexican fudge
directions: In 9 x 9-inch pan, place 1/2 of cheese, then pour mixture of eggs and salsa on top.
Place remaining cheese on top of eggs and salsa.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter and add next 5 items.
Gradually add milk and sour cream.
Cook until thick and add cheese and cooked beans.
Put in casserole and cover with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rommegrot (norwegian porridge)(scandinavian foods, international cuisine?)
directions: Boil cream 20 minutes on low-medium, then add flour slowly, stirring constantly.
In a few minutes, the butter will separate and come to the top.
Remove some of it and add the boiling milk. Ladle into dishes and pour butter on top.
Sprinkle liberally with sugar and cinnamon and serve.
Makes 2 generous servings.

title: sunday best pancakes
directions: Separate eggs, beat whites until stiff.
Put yolks in large bowl and beat well.
Add buttermilk and melted butter, beat.
Sift dry ingredients and add to liquid in bowl and mix until smooth. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Fry on hot grill.
`May use regular milk, instead of buttermilk.

title: homemade lasagne
directions: Brown beef and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 4 eggs, oil, pudding and club soda.
Beat together 2 to 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° until done (about 30 minutes).

title: western baked beans
directions: In skillet, saute beef and onions in oleo until onions are tender.
Combine beans and remaining ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in meat mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, stirring once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend the cream cheese.
Add butter and lemon juice; mix with cream cheese.
Add sugar and mace; mix.

title: penthouse casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add soup, chicken, mushrooms, milk and onion.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole; top with bread crumbs tossed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: fusilli with sausage, spinach & peppers(low fat)
directions: Cook pasta, meanwhile crumble sausage into a large nonstick skillet.
Cook, breaking apart with a wooden spoon until no longer pink.
Add the spinach, red peppers, basil, salt and pepper.
Heat to serving temperature about 3 minutes.
Drain fusilli, add to sausage mixture and toss to combine. serve with garlic bread.

title: pork and sauerkraut supper
directions: Over medium heat, cook pork chops (add salt and pepper to taste) in oil until browned. Remove to plate.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients; mix well. Set aside 1 cup for topping. Pat the remaining mixture into a greased 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan. Prepare brownie batter according to package directions. Spread over the crust. Sprinkle with reserved oat mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack. Cut into bars.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix
eggs, sugar, brown sugar, oil, raisins, pecans and zucchini.
Sift
flour,
baking
powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix
all together with vanilla.
Bake in a greased muffin tin 25 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt, pumpkin pie spice and baking soda. Beat together until fluffy butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in all at once flour mixture and applesauce; beat well.
Stir in raisins and oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until cookies are browned.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together, place in casserole dish and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Place in oven heated to 350° and heat until cheese is melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In oleo, saute chopped onion, chopped celery and chopped bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mock salmon
directions: Fillet fish; wash and dry, cut in 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Combine other ingredients and mix well and add to each quart jar, put all in jars.
Pressure at 15 pounds for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 7 quarts.

title: chocolate bundt
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, oil, vanilla and rum.
Beat 5 minutes; batter will be stiff.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Spoon into a greased and floured 2-quart Bundt pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Then turn out; serve warm or cold, plain or with vanilla ice cream.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sizzling sausage stir-fry
directions: Cook rice and keep warm.
Saute vegetables in oil until crisp and tender.
Add sausage and season to taste.
Heat thoroughly. Mix in 1/2 cup cheese.
Serve over warm rice, sprinkling with remaining cheese.

title: hot apple dish
directions: Don't throw away those leftover mashed potatoes.
Put in refrigerator for another day.
For 1 to 2 cups of potatoes, put 1 egg and chopped onion (in amount to suit you).
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon into heated skillet with small amount of fat.
Let brown, then turn to brown other side.
You will never know they were leftover potatoes.

title: cheese ball
directions: In a separate bowl, mix together the cream cheese, onion and pimentos.
Refrigerate.
In saucepan, mix other ingredients; cook until pasty.
Mix with cream cheese.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped or ground walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Stir and mix good.
Add a few more tablespoons of orange juice, enough to set it good.
Press down firmly in a Pyrex dish or loaf pan.
Leave in icebox.

title: south of the border corn
directions: Boil corn.
Combine remaining ingredients, keeping warm. Place cooked ears on platter and brush with margarine mixture.

title: good peanut icing
directions: Mix
and add evaporated milk to make desired thickness. Beat well.

title: molded orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water until dissolved.
Add orange juice; chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients; chill until firm in a mold or bowl.
Serve with or without mayonnaise, salad dressing or sour cream dressing.
Serves 6.

title: fresh peach sauce
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, mix crushed peaches, sugar and orange juice.
Place over high heat and stir until boiling.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer for 15 minutes or until thick without covering.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Makes 2 cups.
Serve warm on pound cake or over vanilla ice cream.

title: creamy pasta with broccoli, cauliflower and mushrooms
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, cook cauliflower and broccoli until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
With a slotted spoon, remove vegetables and save the liquid for cooking the pasta.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Saute garlic for 2 minutes over medium heat. Add mushrooms for about 5 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and cauliflower.
Saute for 2 to 3 minutes longer; set aside. Meanwhile in reserved boiling vegetable liquid, cook pasta.
Add water if necessary tender but until firm, about 8 to 10 minutes. Drain.
In a food processor combine cottage cheese, milk, sour cream and Parmesan.
Pour over broccoli mixture, add drained pasta and toss until mixed.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Make 8 servings.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar; add eggs and milk.
Sift flour and baking powder and blend with liquid ingredients.
Add vanilla. Divide batter into 3 parts.
To part one, add green food coloring. Pour into loaf pan.
To part two, add red food coloring, then pour this carefully over first layer.
Pour last layer as is carefully over pink layer.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine shortening and boiling water. Stir until shortening is melted. Add salt and sugar. Beat eggs until frothy; beat in cold water. Soften yeast in lukewarm water. Combine cool fat mixture, eggs and yeast; add flour. Knead until glossy. Put in greased bowl; cover and chill overnight. Shape; let rise and bake as for standard rolls. Makes 36.

title: bird seed cones
directions: Tie a length of string around the round end of each cone so that you can later hang it from feeder or tree.
Using knife or wooden paddle, coat pine cone with peanut butter.
Pour bird seed into flat container.
Roll pine cones in bird seed.
Hang.
Birds love both the seeds and peanut butter.

title: salmon stew
directions: Mash salmon up good.
Put into 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Add milk, margarine and 2 cans water.
Let boil for 5 to 10 minutes. Add pepper.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar.
Cream together well.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Place on wire rack to cool completely before serving.

title: apple slices
directions: Mix oleo with flour.
Roll out flat with rolling pin.
Line the bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with 1/2 of rolled dough.
Crush 6 squares of graham crackers and sprinkle over dough.
Slice 6 to 8 apples and mix with 1 cup sugar.
Put apples over graham crumbs and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put the rest of the rolled dough on top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: meatballs
directions: Put the ground beef in a large bowl; add eggs, parsley, nutmeg, salt and cheese.
Wet the bread well and squeeze out the water and shred it into the meat mixture.
Discard too crusty crusts.
Mix well.
Form into balls about the size of a large egg. Flatten so they are not more than 1-inch thick in the middle. Cover well with bread crumbs.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt one stick of butter then add cream cheese, melt together. Slowly pour in milk and heat on medium heat slowly adding Parmesan cheese and pepper. Heat until well blended then pour over your favorite pound of pasta. Add cooked broccoli and chicken.

title: peanut butter snackers
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In large saucepan, combine corn syrup and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until completely mixed.
Stir in cereal and peanuts until evenly coated.
Press gently into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes into quarters.
Place potatoes in large saucepan and cover with water and boil until tender, about 8 minutes; drain well.
While potatoes are cooking combine salad dressing, sour cream, 1 c. Cheddar cheese and bacon in a large bowl.
Add potatoes and salt.
Spoon potato and cream mixture into a 9
13 baking dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 c. cheese.
Bake potato mixture until bubbly, about 20-30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Bake chicken and drain oil.
Boil noodles.
Mix soups together and add 2 cups of water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften and beat with mixer; add nuts and roll.
If too soft, refrigerate before shaping it.
Then roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: hop scotch
directions: Place peanut butter and chips in pan over low heat; stir until blended.
Add marshmallows and noodles.
Stir until melted.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper; chill until set.

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit cocktail, apples, bananas, mandarin oranges, mini marshmallows and walnuts.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and stir. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sherry pound cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add cake mix, pudding, nutmeg and oil. Beat 10 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan while hot.
Pierce with fork and pour mixture of powdered sugar and sherry over cake. Serve hot or let cool!

title: fat-free banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the dry ingredients together; set aside.
Mix the honey and applesauce together.
Add the egg replacer mixture, banana, raisins and walnuts.
Add the wet mixture to the dry and mix well.
Turn into a nonstick 13 x 9-inch pan and flatten slightly with a spatula.
Bake for 1 hour, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; drain and set aside.
Saute onion and celery.
Add browned meat and all other ingredients.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine in a pan; add 1 1/2 cups of herb seasoned stuffing mix. Stir enough to mix.
Sprinkle on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: new england dinner(stove top)
directions: Cover meat with cold water.
Simmer 3 hours, adding the potatoes, carrots and cabbage the last hour.
Drain and serve. Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn puff curls
directions: Boil 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour over corn curl and nut mixture. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes. They are ready to eat and delicious!

title: baked beef brisket
directions: Combine all ingredient and marinate.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours or until meat is tender.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order:
oranges, pineapple, marshmallows, sour cream, coconut and cherries.
Chill.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients to softened cream cheese except almonds.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Great served with your favorite crackers.

title: easy fried rice
directions: In a nonstick skillet, put olive oil.
Turn temperature to 450°.
Put carrot and potato.
Stir until cooked.
Add salt to taste, then add frozen peas.
Stir and salt.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Stir until mixed real well.
Salt to taste.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir in pecans and fruit. Pour into pie shells and refrigerate several hours.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and Ramen noodle seasoning. Pour over slaw and Ramen noodles.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Let the margarine get soft, then blend with sugar and lemon extract.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix gradually.
Add flour. Mix all these together.
Add Seven-Up soda and beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour in a greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Take out of the oven.
Let it cool.
Take it out of pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Mix 2 cups brown sugar, butter, eggs, salt, vanilla, soda in hot water and flour together to make dough.
May need more flour to work with.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Mix together in saucepan 2 cups brown sugar, raisins, water, salt and flour.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Roll dough thin.
Cut in three inch rounds.
Place on greased baking sheet, put a rounded teaspoon of filling in center.
Place another piece of dough on top.
Press to seal edges. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Add following 6 ingredients to macaroni.
Mix Miracle Whip, mustard, milk and salt and pepper.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: easy cherry struedel
directions: Pour cherry pie filling in bottom of cake pan.
Pour dry cake mix over cherries. Do not stir.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix. Sprinkle pecans or oatmeal all over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let cool or eat warm with ice cream.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a jar.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Pour in browned ground beef.
Add onion, vegetables and Tater Tots.
Pour mushroom soup over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix garlic, basil, oregano and salt with breadcrumbs and place on large plate.
Melt 1/4 cup of the margarine; dip each chicken breast in the melted margarine and roll in breadcrumbs.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake near center of oven 30 to 45 minutes or until fully cooked.
Melt the remaining 1/4 cup margarine.
Mix in wine and green onions.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Return chicken to oven for 3 to 5 minutes or until sauce is hot.
Serve over rice.

title: raisin cake
directions: Place in saucepan the shortening, boiling water and raisins. Boil together for 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Place chicken broth, onion and vegetable in large kettle. Simmer until vegetable is tender.
Add seasonings and mushroom soup.
Stir gently.
Serve when completely mixed.

title: cookout meal in a pouch
directions: Divide meat into 6 lumps.
Place each lump on a separate square of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Flatten it out and shape into a patty.
Top each patty with a desired amount of carrots, sliced potatoes and top with one onion slice, if desired.
Form package with foil.
Cook until done on grill or in coals at a cookout. Will be a hit!
Fun and good!
Serves 6.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk in large bowl.
Add Cool Whip; mix until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Line a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with graham crackers.
Layer as follows:
layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding mix (approximately 1/2 of mix), layer of graham crackers, the rest of pudding mix and another layer of graham crackers.
Spread with icing.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla; beat until smooth. Pour batter into square pan, 8 x 8 x 2 or 9 x 9 x 2-inches.

In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle mixture evenly over batter. Pour hot water over top; do not stir. Bake 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Let stand 15 minutes; spoon into dessert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top. Whipped cream or ice cream are nice toppings.

title: creamy carrot-potato boat
directions: Bake potatoes in a 375 degree oven about 45 minutes or until tender, cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out each half leaving a thin shell.
In a small mixing bowl combine potato pulp, carrots, cream cheese, 1 T. milk and pepper. Beat until smooth; add more milk if necessary.
Chop tops of green onion tops.
Put potato back in potato shells; sprinkle onion on top.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine salad oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Add flour and mix thoroughly. Add apple, vanilla, nuts, raisins and spices. Mix well. Grease pan dusted with flour. Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add the vinegar and food coloring; beat well.
Sift the flour, soda, salt and cocoa together; add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla; beat well. Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cream the margarine and cream cheese in a bowl; add remaining vanilla.
Sift the powdered sugar; add to the creamed mixture gradually.
Add nuts; mix well.
Spread on top of cake layers and place layers together.
Spread on side of cake.

title: crustless salmon quiche
directions: Toss salmon, cheese and onion with flour; spread in greased pie plate.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients. Pour egg mixture over salmon mixture.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: crazy coconut cream pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together with electric mixer. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Let stand 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes it's own crust.

title: quick and easy "batter" bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and 2 cups of flour.
Blend well.
Beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape batter from sides of bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 30 minutes.
Stir dough batter by beating 25 to 30 strokes. Spread evenly in greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Smooth top by patting in shape with floured hands.
Cover.
Let rise until double, about 40 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Brush top with melted butter.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: cubed steak parmegiana
directions: Coat steaks in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Combine cracker crumbs, basil and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese in small bowl. Mix egg with 2 tablespoons water in a bowl.
Dip each steak into egg mixture.
Coat each steak evenly with crumb mixture.
Heat oil in a 13 x 9-inch pan in a 375° oven 5 to 10 minutes.
Place steaks in baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Pour off drippings.
Combine tomato sauce with sugar, garlic and ground oregano, pouring mixture over steaks. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 minutes longer. Top with Mozzarella cheese and a sprinkle of leaf oregano.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring water to boil in large saucepan; add bouillon cubes and stir until dissolved.
Stir in soy sauce; return to boil.
Remove from heat; add eggs all at once, stirring rapidly in one direction with spoon (egg will separate to form fine threads).
Stir in green onion.
Serve immediately.
Makes 12 cups.

title: basic 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: *Use 2 teaspoons of coconut flavoring when baking coconut cake instead of vanilla.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Mix butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs gradually.
Batter will be stiff.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: norwegian lace cookies
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan and pour over oatmeal.
Beat egg until light and beat in the sugar.
Mix together the flour and baking powder and stir into the egg mixture along with the oatmeal mixture.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls of batter onto greased and floured baking sheet, 2 or 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and let stand about 1 minute.
Quickly lift out cookies.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook on slow heat until berries are tender the sugar, water and blueberries.
Add cornstarch mixed with a little water.
Cook until thick.
Let cool and pour in a cooked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip or your favorite topping.

title: pumpkin bread(from home grown pumpkin)
directions: Bake in 2 greased pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: maude hyde's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; cream well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together; reserve enough flour to dredge nuts and dates well.
Add flour to the creamed mixture.
Add balance of nuts, apples and dates.
Add vanilla last.
Batter will be stiff, but apples will supply the moisture.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or when tested with a pick.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut
up
chicken,
put	in
pan.
Add
vegetables.
Mix chicken broth with soup and pour
over chicken and vegetables. Mix Bisquick, milk and butter together.
Pour over chicken and vegetables (spread over top, it spreads
thin).
Bake
for	45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round layer cake pans or one 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large mixer bowl, combine margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking powder.
Add alternately with water to sugar mixture until well blended.
Stir in candy, if desired.
Pour equal portions into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool thoroughly.
Fill and frost with One Bowl Buttercream Frosting.
Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles, about 30 minutes.

title: "june's" chicken tortilla casserole
directions: No proportions are given.
Amounts are strictly optional in accordance with how many you are serving.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine the first 8 ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Blend milk and flour; add to vegetables.
Cook until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.

title: chicago crunchy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt onto waxed paper.
Preheat oven to moderate (350°).
Beat butter, margarine, sugars, egg, milk and vanilla in bowl until well blended.
Stir flour mixture alternately with oil in sugar and butter mixture until mixture is thoroughly mixed.
Stir in cornflakes, oats and chocolate.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets, 2-inches apart. Bake in preheated oven for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: parmesan stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and chop very fine.
Mix stems with bread crumbs.
Cut onion in half and scrape.
Cut side with edge of knife to obtain the pulp.
Mix it in.
Mix garlic very fine and mix it in.
Add parsley, salt, pepper and oregano.
Stuff the mushroom caps with mixture.
Pour a little of the oil into baking dish.
Place caps in and then sprinkle with the rest of the oil. Place in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Sprinkle with coconut and then chocolate chips, then butterscotch chips.
Pour milk evenly over entire mixture. Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: chicken indonesia
directions: Mix all ingredients together in any kind of baking dish (Pyrex, Correll).
This is a one pan dinner.
Bake, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve alone or over rice.
The kids will love it.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, whisk together mayonnaise and sour cream.
Stir in artichoke hearts, grated Parmesan cheese, chopped pimientos and hot pepper sauce.
Spoon into an ovenproof baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with crackers or French bread slices, if desired.
Makes 2 cups (11 servings).

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg, drain off fat and add taco seasoning.
Simmer as directed on package.
Remove from stove; place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add Mozzarella cheese onto the hot hamburg, so it can melt some.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in half.
Crumble 1/2 of the cake into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread pie filling over the cake.
Crumble the other half of the cake on top of the pie filling.
Prepare the instant pudding according to the directions, but use 1/2 cup less milk.
Add the sour cream and mix together.
Pour over the top layer of the angel food cake.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Trim off green and pink portions of watermelon. Cut into 1-inch pieces. Parboil until tender but not soft; drain. Combine ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour over rinds; let stand 2 nights in succession, draining off liquid, heating it and pouring it over rinds each morning.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix drained fruit with marshmallows.
Combine eggs, flour, sugar, fruit juice and butter.
Bring to boil.
Cool.
Add whipped cream and mix with fruit.
Chill.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix together and shape into log all ingredients, except pecans.
Roll log in pecans and chill.
Great with crackers.

title: butterscotch clusters
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in peanuts and noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: amish bread starter
directions: Stir, then pour 3 (1 cup) portions into 3 containers and give to 3 friends and use 1 cup to make Amish Bread.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large plastic bag; shake until well coated.
Empty bag into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, stirring occasionally. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer, until potatoes are brown and tender.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil and peel yams.
Cut into quarters lengthwise.
Place in shallow buttered pan.
Pour syrup over yams and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute pepper, mushrooms, zucchini, garlic and onion in oil until tender, but still crisp; cool.
Beat eggs with cream; add cheeses, bread, salt, pepper and vegetables (should be fairly thick).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.
Very rich dish!!

title: biscuits
directions: Mix biscuit mix, cheese and milk to a soft dough. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown (following directions on biscuit mix box). Mix margarine and garlic powder and brush over biscuits before removing them from the cookie sheet. Serve immediately. Yield: 12 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and add buttermilk, juice and vanilla.
Mix in with beater until uniform in color and texture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or smaller pan and bake at 350° until tests done with toothpick.

title: japanese spaghetti
directions: In a heavy casserole or pot, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from pot and drain on paper towels.
Reserve bacon drippings in pot.
Add cabbage to bacon drippings; simmer over low heat, covered, until soft.
Add mushrooms, soy sauce, garlic, seasonings and scallions (including the green tops).
Simmer until vegetables are soft.
Toss with spaghetti and crumbled bacon.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy mushroom appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the mushrooms and cream cheese; add salt and pepper to taste.
Cut each crescent triangle in half, then in half again so that you have four triangles from each original one.
Fill triangle with one teaspoon of the cream cheese mixture.
Bring three points of the triangle together and pinch.
Brush each appetizer with egg and sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake on a cookie sheet (greased) for 10 minutes or until browned. Yields 32 appetizers.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Place cooked broccoli in a buttered, 1-quart casserole. Arrange chicken pieces over broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread crumbs over surface.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.

title: sopa de fideo
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 300°.
Melt shortening.
Saute vermicelli until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Add beef and cook, stirring until meat loses red color.
Stir in next 8 ingredients.
Add tomatoes and water.
Stir gently.

title: lo-cal bread pudding
directions: Cut bread in half in casserole dish. Beat all other ingredients, except nutmeg.
Pour over bread.
Shake on nutmeg. Bake at 350° until set and knife comes out clean.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Place half of noodles on bottom of casserole. Mix tuna, celery, onion and cashews and put on top of noodles. Add mushroom soup (rinse with 1/4 cup water). Put remaining noodles on top. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add other dry ingredients. Stir in flour, one cup at a time.
Add 1 cup milk as dough gets stiff.
Keep adding flour to get stiff dough.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions, sprinkle the salt over and let stand for 1 hour.
Rinse in cold water.
Combine other ingredients.
Heat to boiling point.
Put in tomatoes and onions. Bring to boil again.
Fill jars and seal.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put
all
ingredients
in a mixing bowl and stir or use slowest
speed
to mix.
Bake in a pie shell for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: fiesta black beans and rice
directions: In a 3-quart Dutch oven, bring 1/4 cup chicken broth to a boil.
Add onion and garlic. Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes or until tender. Stir in remaining chicken broth, peppers, chiles, beans, rice and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with minced cilantro. Yields 6 servings.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix above ingredients, pour into pie crust and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche(bisquick)
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Put in ham.
Sprinkle with onion and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Place remaining ingredients in blender for 15 seconds; pour over ham mix.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat oleo and Crisco with sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and salt to creamed mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture on medium speed.
Fold in coconut.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until toothpick stuck in center comes clean.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
When cool, slice in three layers.

title: holiday breakfast(serve warm)
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, and 1 tsp. cinnamon in 9 x 13 pan. Add apples and raisins. Toss to coat well. Spread apples evenly over bottom of pan. Arrange sliced bread on top. Mix eggs, milk, vanilla, and remaining 2 tsp. cinnamon until well blended. Pour over bread, soaking completely. Cover and refrigerate 4 to 24 hours. Bake covered with aluminum foil in preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes. Uncover and bake 5 more minutes. Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together.
Use for dipping any raw veggies.
Best if made at least 2 hours before using.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: meat balls stuffed with green peppers
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Stuff one olive into each ball and smooth beef mixture around olive.
Brown in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Meat balls can be refrigerated for up to one week.
Makes 25 meat balls.

title: texas' favorite party dip
directions: Saute ground beef
and onions until brown.
Drain well. Add remaining ingredients
and stir over low heat until cheese melts. Serve in fondue
dish
or
slow
cooker to keep piping hot.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Keep on low heat.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil in a large skillet.
Add 2 cups water, beef bouillon cubes and onion.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: marshmallow rolls(makes great holiday gifts.)
directions: Cut each marshmallow into small pieces into a large bowl. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Melt the chocolate and butter together and pour over the marshmallows.
Add the nuts.
Mix all together with a large spoon.
On a piece of wax paper, sprinkle 2 or 3 tablespoons coconut.
Take out 1/3 of the mixture to form a roll on the wax paper with your hands, about 2-inches in diameter. (It's messy, but good enough to be worth it.)
Roll in the coconut and wrap tightly in the wax paper.
Put in the refrigerator.
When it is solid, cut in slices about 1/2-inch thick as you need it.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, melt butter; add meat, onion and garlic. Cook until meat is done.
Stir in flour, soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat to serving temperature.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Melt chocolate in boiling water and add to mixture.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk (including soda and buttermilk). Add vanilla and salt.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Fill and ice with German Chocolate Icing.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Save enough dough for top crust.

title: "dip" to use with fruit
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme together until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit (banana, pineapple, apples, strawberries, etc.).

title: sister's banana bread
directions: Cream the margarine, eggs and sugar. Add the flour, bananas and water; mix well. Add the vanilla and the pecans. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: picante sauce
directions: Boil 5 minutes; heat and boil lids and rings.
Seal.
Makes 12 pints.

title: pork chops and orange rice
directions: Brown pork chops in heavy skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Place rice in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over the rice.
Arrange browned pork chops on rice.
Pour chicken soup over all.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: basil grilled chicken
directions: Press 3/4 teaspoon of pepper into meaty sides of breast halves.
Combine 1/3 cup melted butter and 1/4 cup chopped basil. Stir well.
Brush chicken lightly with melted butter mixture.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Do not use a mixer on this cake.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into two balls.
Roll in cup of nuts.
Chill overnight for easier rolling.

title: new england's finest clam chowder
directions: Saute the bacon until almost crispy.
Add the onions and continue to cook until onions become transparent.
Add the potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium flame, uncovered, for 12 to 15 minutes or until the potatoes are soft. Drain and chop the clams, reserving the liquid.
Add the clams, 3/4 cup clam liquid, butter and half and half to the potato mixture. Mix well.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes over a medium flame.
Serves 6.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter together for 2 1/2 minutes in the microwave. Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together. Add melted mixture into it, beating well. Add vanilla and chopped nuts and place in a buttered 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Cook rump roast in crock-pot for about 5 hours on high setting.
Drain the dripping and add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add beef that has been sliced and cooled.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 days, occasionally basting beef with marinade.
Serve on hoagie rolls or French bread.

title: four chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding together.
Beat in eggs, oil and water. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan or a Bundt pan with nonstick spray.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with chocolate or fudge frosting.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Cream sugar, oil and egg yolks together.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add egg whites to creamed mixture. Fold together.
Add chocolate, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put into an oiled baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rumford biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Rub in shortening as lightly as possible with fingers, just working until the fat is blended with flour.
Then mix a very soft dough with liquids (keeping liquid as cold as possible).
Mix with pastry blender or knife rather than spoon or hand, as blades or knife edge is colder and also because it cuts and mixes the dough more thoroughly.
Turn the dough onto a well floured board and roll or pat with hand until about 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into biscuit and lay them not touching on a baking pan.
Bake in quick (about 400°) oven 12 to 14 minutes.

title: yum - yum salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: super cheese straws
directions: Beat butter and shortening thoroughly.
Add very finely grated cheese; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Blend flour, salt and cayenne pepper together.
Add in 3 additions.
Mix well after each addition.
Make a roll of dough. Press into cookie tube firmly.
Hold cookie maker firmly; press. Bake at 350° approximately 12 minutes.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: microwave swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in 6 pieces, then coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Place in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover with onion. Break up tomatoes with fork and pour over top.
Cover.
Microwave at medium power level for 60 to 70 minutes, rearranging meat after 30 minutes, until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot.
Boil 3 minutes.
After it starts boiling place in a bowl of ice water to thicken.
Put in pecans and place in a buttered dish.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, salt and water to soft ball stage.
Add peanuts.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes until well mixed. Remove from heat. Add baking soda and beat quickly with spoon.
Pour onto greased jelly roll pan.
Spread.
Cool and break.

title: baked hominy and cheese
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg.
Add hominy, cheese, milk, onion, bacon, butter and pepper; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 45 minutes or until bubbly and top begins to brown.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo, egg and nuts and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all of remaining ingredients thoroughly and pour over
the
other
ingredients already pressed in the pan.
Bake 1 hour
at
Cool and cut in pieces the size you want to serve.
You
can
cut in small pieces or a little larger with a scoop of Cool Whip.

title: make 'em some pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, beat milk and other ingredients with mixer or wire whisk.
Pour into crust and bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Cool and garnish.
Can be frozen.

title: graham streusel coffee cake
directions: Combine the first five ingredients; set aside.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of the batter into a greased 13 x 9 baking pan.
Sprinkle with half of the graham cracker mixture.
Carefully spoon the remaining batter on top. Sprinkle with the remaining graham cracker mixture.

title: baked chicken(for diabetics)
directions: Arrange chicken breast halves in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture over batter.
Then top with rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter with sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift cocoa with flour, baking powder and salt; work into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and bake 30 to 35 minutes in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, or just until pulls from sides.
Cool to room temperature upright in pan on a wire rack. Cut into 16 squares and serve.

title: fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter, salt and vanilla to a rapid boil in large pan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add to sugar mixture the chocolate bar, marshmallows, chocolate chips and pecans.
Stir and mix rapidly until all ingredients are blended in.
Put fudge into a large cake pan greased with butter (13 x 9-inch or larger).
It sets very fast.
Cut into squares.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Beat together all ingredients, except shrimp.
Fold in shrimp last.
Serve with rye party bread.

title: quick sweet and sour supper
directions: Cook and stir chicken and garlic in hot oil in large skillet or wok until tender and lightly browned, about 7 minutes.
Stir in scallions, preserves and chili sauce.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.
Supposed to feed 4; 2 or 3 is more like it.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients in one bowl.
Cream sugar and oil in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add pumpkin and beat in well.
Add dry ingredients.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Pull dough away from center with a spoon.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sausage dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate biscuits into 10 biscuits. Roll or press each into 4-inch circle.
Spread with margarine. Combine cheese and oregano.
Sprinkle over biscuits.
Place sausage on biscuit.
Roll biscuit around sausage.
Cut into 3 or 4 pieces.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: spicy pumpkin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat cake mix, oats, margarine, sugar and 1 egg until crumbly.
Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish; bake 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: When I baked, after the first rising and the loaves had been formed, I reserved enough of the dough for several "muffins."
I then fried these in a small amount of oil.
Delicious served with brown beans and ham, etc.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread mixture of avocados, mayo and garlic salt on bottom of dish.
Add sour cream and taco seasoning as second layer.
Add cheeses as next layer.
Sprinkle tomatoes, onions and olives on top.
Use as dip with Tostitos.
Best when comes to room temperature.

title: tasty meatball-oven style
directions: Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
The soup adds most of the seasoning.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Bring these ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly. Spread on cake.
Place iced cake under broiler for a few minutes. Remove and cool.

title: shrimp quiches(24 mini quiches)
directions: Lightly grease 2 dozen 1 3/4-inch mini muffin cups.
Separate flake rolls into 12 equal pieces.
Cut each in half.
Press each into bottom and sides of muffin cups, making small pinched lip. Divide shrimp evenly among pastry shells.

title: mary's frosted pecans
directions: Beat egg white and salt until stiff. Add sugar and mix. Fold pecans into mixture, coating well. Melt butter on cookie sheet or pan; spread pecans evenly and bake at 325° for 20 minutes, turning every 10 minutes. Be careful not to burn. Put pecans in paper bag and shake to prevent sticking together.

title: spiked strawberries
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Pour mixture over strawberries. Let stand for 10 minutes, then drain.

title: oatmeal banana muffins
directions: In a bowl, mix butter, eggs, bananas and honey.
Mix together yogurt and baking soda. Add to mixture and cream.
Add flour to creamed mixture and stir just until blended.
Stir in oatmeal. Fill muffin cup 2/3 full of filling. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: mozzarella chicken(serve over rice)
directions: Cut up chicken; remove the skin.
Use mainly the breast, thighs and legs.
In large electric skillet, melt butter.
Add garlic.
Sprinkle on bottom of skillet.
Now add cut-up chicken. Simmer until lightly brown on one side.

title: chicken breasts with bacon
directions: Spread bottom of buttered casserole dish with 8 pieces of dried beef.
Roll chicken breasts in bacon and place on top
of beef. In blender, mix soups, celery and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and bake for about 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Great over egg noodles.

title: chili cheese ball
directions: Place Velveeta cheese and cream cheese in a large bowl.
Let come to room temperature.
Mix cheeses well.
Add nuts, garlic powder and salt; mix well.
Shape into ball; roll in chili powder. Wrap in foil; chill until firm.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice and peel apples and place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with mixture of flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and unbeaten egg (which has been mixed with fork until crumbly).
Next pour melted butter all over top of mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in preheated oven at 350° or until apples are soft (great with milk or ice cream).

title: fruit bowl
directions: Drain all fruit well. Combine with pie filling in a large bowl.

title: mincemeat(canning or freezing)
directions: Cook beef thoroughly.
Do not brown.
Put meat and apples through metal blade of food processor.
Return to cooking pot. Add all the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Bring to boil. Lower heat.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 pints.
Can be canned.
Process for 60 minutes at 10 pounds of pressure.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Then sift together rest of ingredients and stir into first mixture. Form balls the size of walnuts. Place about 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: red apple inn rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over butter, sugar and salt.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat in eggs.
Add to cooled mixture.
Add flour and mix.
This will be very thin.
Let stand overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Shape 2 hours before baking. Brush with melted butter and bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream together zucchini, sugar, oil and eggs. Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture. Pour into well-greased and sugared Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/3 hours. Immediately after removing from oven, run knife around edge of pan and center to loosen cake. Let cool completely before removing from pan. Pour Vanilla Glaze over and let set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly, but well.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix together.
Add nuts; mix well.
Divide batter into 2-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Use mixer for this.
Add coconut, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Heat oven to 350°; bake one hour.

title: hot dog slaw
directions: Mix all together.
Let boil 20 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Good on hot dogs.

title: my mother's orange cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add slightly beaten egg whites. Mix flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Pour into two 8 or 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and spread filling between layers and on top of cake.

title: peach jam
directions: Peel and pit 3 pounds peaches.
Use grinder to chop in 1/4-inch pieces.
Measure peaches; add lemon juice and sugar.
Bring mixture to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Then add Certo and margarins; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Skim foam off.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 8 cups.

title: southern hash
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for almost 1 hour. Easy to burn, watch it.
Serves 16.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spread crescent roll dough on 13-inch baking stone or pizza pan and pinch seams together.
Bake for 10 - 15 minutes until brown.
Remove from oven and let cool completely.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until blended. Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture. Chill.
Cut into wedges or squares.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick and moist bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine flour and sugar.
Add the sour cream and beer alternately; mix well.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
I divide mine into 2 loaves. Bake for 45 minutes; brush top with butter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes more.
Let cool slightly.
Serve warm, cool or sliced and toasted.

title: angel food cake layer
directions: On a platter or baking sheet, place angel food cake.
Spread 1/2 vanilla pudding, sprinkle 1/2 of crushed pineapple and spread 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Place in refrigerator for 12 hours. Freeze for 2 hours, then thaw.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Arrange chicken breast in baking dish. Mix together the mustard, molasses, vinegar, soy sauce, crushed pineapple and brown sugar.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour (basting frequently) or until chicken is tender.

title: mango bread
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients all at once in large mixing bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into two bread pans coated with Pam spray.
Bake for one hour, or until knife comes out clean.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill overnight.
Spread remaining topping over pudding.
Makes 15 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until tender.
Remove from broth and cut up.
Save broth, setting aside 1/2 cup for later use. In broth, cook the spaghetti until tender and drain.
In skillet, cook onion and bell pepper in margarine until tender but not brown. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add soup, tomatoes, English peas, chicken and spaghetti, stirring after each addition.
Now add the 1/2 cup of broth saved earlier.
Stir mixture well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly (approximately 30 minutes).

title: corn pancakes or waffles
directions: Preheat griddle or waffle iron.
Grease lightly.
Blend muffin mix, egg, shortening and milk.
Bake on hot griddle or waffle iron.

title: ultra quick lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine tomato sauce, garlic and oregano in a bowl.
In another bowl, beat the eggs.
Then beat in Ricotta, Parmesan
and nutmeg.
Pour a generous amount of sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish/pan.
Alternate lasagna, sauce, cheese mixture and Mozzarella, making layers ending with Mozzarella.
Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 hour, remove foil and bake another 15 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes before cutting.

title: smothered venison
directions: Brown sliced steaks in skillet.
Saute small onion.
Add venison, tomatoes and onion to crock-pot.
Cook on low heat until meat falls into small pieces (bite-size).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice with garlic toast or bread.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil or bake chicken breasts until done.
Chop into bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli, drain and put in bottom of deep casserole dish.
Spread chicken on top.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until mixture is bubbly.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Pour into
a
greased casserole and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Mix cornbread mix, eggs and milk.
Lightly brown ground beef with onion.
Put half of the cornbread mixture in a lightly greased pan; spread meat mixture on top and cover with half of cheese. Spread the other half of cornbread mix and cover with the rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese; gradually add cream and beat until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients and blend.
Chill.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: p-nut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for about two hours.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together well. Drop by large spoonfuls into frying pan and brown well on both sides. Sprinkle with grated cheese and cover until melted.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion in fat.
Add next 7 ingredients. Cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Put noodles in the bottom of a baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Cover with sauce, then Ricotta cheese. Cover with grated Swiss cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss with first mixture and chill for 2 hours.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring 4 cups water to a boil.
Add 3 3/4 cups sugar and boil 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and take a little of the mixture and stir in 1/2 cup instant coffee.
Return to burner and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and allow mixture to cool for several minutes.
Stir in 1/5 of vodka.
Split whole vanilla bean lengthwise and place in 1/2 gallon jug.
Pour hot mixture into jug and cap.
Let stand for 2 weeks.
Remove the vanilla bean and drink!

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat and drain. Add onions, McCormick seasonings and tomatoes. Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour. Blend beans until creamy and add to chili. Cook 30 to 45 minutes more.

title: easiest ever dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
If desired, add chopped parsley, pimiento or dry onion soup mix.
Chill.

title: noodle clusters
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: salsa
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
