Use plastic gloves and keep away from face.
Chop and cook peppers in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
For milder sauce, drain water and boil again with fresh water.
Mix cornstarch with a little water.
Slowly add to peppers.
Mix the rest of ingredients and cook until it thickens.

title: jello salad supreme
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add strawberries (still frozen).
Add pineapple and banana.
Mix well.
Pour half of mixture in Jell-O mold.
Place in freezer for 30 to 40 minutes to set.
Spread with 1 to 1 1/2 cups of sour cream.
Pour rest of Jell-O mixture on top and refrigerate.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Add water as needed. Boil for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut-chocolate meringue bars
directions: Combine butter, sugar, 1/2 c. brown sugar, egg yolks and vanilla in large mixing bowl; beat until thoroughly blended.

title: cook's salad
directions: Blend Cool Whip and pudding together.
Crush cookies in bowl. Add the cocktail with juice.
Add Cool Whip and pudding mixture. Stir and chill.
Goes with anything.

title: signe espling spritz
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until very light.
Add eggs and beat lightly.
Add almond extract and vanilla.
Then add flour sifted with baking powder.
Beat until very light.
Put through cookie press in desired shapes onto cookie sheet.
Shapes are usually in O's or S's.
Bake until light in color.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and cool.

title: summer stew
directions: Cut meat into bite size chunks and place in a large bowl. Thaw and drain carrots, onions and beans.
Clean the mushrooms and cut in half.
Cut yellow pepper into strips.
Add these vegetables to the meat.

title: coca-cola chicken(pork is good too)
directions: Lightly brown the meat in a small amount of oil.
Add the soda; do not cover meat (about halfway).
Cover and cook on medium heat about 10 to 15 minutes, turn meat and cook another 10 to 15 minutes (until done).
Add ketchup, mixing with remaining sauce. Remove cover and cook 10 minutes or until chicken is done.	Sauce should be thick.
Add more ketchup if necessary.

title: lazy day cabbage rolls
directions: Chop half of cabbage, cut other half into wedges.
Brown hamburger and onion lightly, drain.
Add rice, tomatoes, soup, water and chopped cabbage.
Mix well, put into casserole.
Put cabbage wedges on top.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven until cabbage is tender.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
Blend in oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Mix coconut, raisins and pecans.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Stir coconut mixture into flour mixture.
Stir all into batter. Grease and flour two bread pans.
Divide mixture between pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: 9-inch strawberry pie
directions: Put the sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O and 7-Up in pan; cook until it thickens.
Set aside and cool.
Pour into baked pie crust. Slice strawberries and lay over the mixture in the pie crust.

title: beer-cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole or grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients, beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Pour into pan of your choice.
Bake approximately 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: bob's crab fondue
directions: Heat all ingredients until melted and bubbly, then dip large chunks of heated French bread into the fondue and devour to your hearts content.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with cornbread.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice evenly over bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Place chicken on top of rice with skin side up.
Mix soup with water.
Pour over chicken, cover and bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: southern-style jambalaya
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot butter in large skillet until lightly browned.
Add sausage, green pepper, onion and celery; cook until vegetables are just tender, about 5 minutes.
Mix in tomatoes and water; bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork; sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tex-mex chicken tenders
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and chili powder; set aside.
In separate bowl, blend egg product and chilies.
Coat chicken with flour; dip into egg mixture.
Coat with cracker crumbs.
Place on greased sheet.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Serve with salsa.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat up hickory nuts very fine until the mixture can be formed into balls.
Place in a saucepan and cover with boiling water. Stir well separating the shells from the "goodies."
Strain through a cloth or fine sieve.
Add either cooked rice or mashed hominy.
Heat and serve in a bowl just as you would soup.
Season with sugar.

title: southern carolina cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter a 9-inch square baking pan. Lightly beat eggs with milk and butter.
Set aside. In another bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar and chili powder.
Stir in milk mixture until combined.
Spread batter evenly into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Insert fork into center.
If it comes out clean, cool in pan.
Cut into pieces and serve.
Makes 24 servings.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Saute onion, celery and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well (extra broth may be needed to make mixture really moist). Bake at 350° until brown (approximately 30 minutes).

title: chow chow
directions: Grind cabbage, peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for 10 minutes.
Squeeze out liquid and add salt and sugar.
Cover with vinegar and boil 5 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: one-pot turkey pie
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together soup and milk.
Stir in turkey, vegetables, basil and pepper.
Bake, covered, in a 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Top with biscuits.
Bake, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes more or until biscuits are golden.
Makes 3 servings.

title: holiday cut-outs
directions: Mix together Crisco, sugar and eggs, then add remaining ingredients.
Chill
in
refrigerator 1 hour.
Roll on floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut	out
in
favorite shapes.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: old fashioned coconut pound cake
directions: Defrost coconut.
Eggs and butter should be at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Spray pan with oil spray. Cream the butter and sugar together well. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well. Add flour, salt, soda, sour cream and vanilla. Blend.
Stir in coconut.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: sue's biscuits
directions: Make a well in center of flour.
Mix together oil and milk; add to flour.
Mix ingredients well, but do not knead!
Pinch off balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll five or six times in palms of hands.
Place about 1-inch apart on small cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Flour backs of fingers and flatten each ball so sides are touching.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: mamaw's pie crust
directions: Mix together and roll out to shape needed.

title: all night sticky buns
directions: Combine the melted margarine and brown sugar; set aside. Grease a round Bundt pan.
Layer ingredients in order listed. Sprinkle dry powder mix over rolls, then pour butter mixture evenly over top.
Place in cold oven at late evening.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat the eggs and add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350 for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Form meat mixture into about 40 meat balls, using a rounded teaspoon for each.
Brown meat balls lightly in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Combine chili sauce and jelly.
Pour over meat balls.
Heat, stirring until jelly is melted.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes until sauce thickens; baste occasionally.
Makes around 40 meat balls.

title: candied carrots(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of salted water. Boil 10 minutes; drain. Combine next 3 ingredients in a medium skillet; cook over low heat, stirring until cranberry sauce melts. Add carrots and stir gently. Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated. Serve hot.

title: sugar nuts
directions: Combine both kinds of sugar and the sour cream in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking, without stirring, to 238° on candy thermometer, or until a little drop of the mixture in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add whichever flavoring you prefer and the walnuts.
Stir gently until all nuts are coated.

title: country soup
directions: In saucepan, place potatoes, carrots, onions, lettuce, celery, basil, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Pass mixture through food mill, strainer or puree in blender.
Measure puree; add 1 cup light cream for every 3 cups puree.
Heat thoroughly.
To serve, top with small lump of butter.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: reuben romanoff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare Romanoff noodles as directed on package except increase milk to 1/2 cup and stir in caraway seed.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Pick full beans.
Snap as if to cook.
Place them on a scaffle out in the sun.
Stir them once or twice a day to dry quickly. When they are real dry, place them in cloth bags and hang them up. Or, you can place them in the freezer.
To cook them, soak overnight.
Next morning, rinse them good.
Good with a chunk of fatback or ham hock with plenty of water.
Salt to taste.
Cook several hours, until beans are tender.

title: thummies (cookies)(you may use your thumb in this one.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and butter to a pie crust consistency.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; mix well.
Form into a ball and chill until firm enough to handle easily.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, onion and eggs.
Layer mixture in large casserole dish.
Mix soup, broth and vegetables.
Pour over chicken mixture.

title: marshmallow rocky road fudge
directions: Butter two 8 x 8-inch cake pans.
Cover bottoms with pecan halves.
Butter sides and bottom of heavy saucepan.

title: bram's frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all together and put in cupcake papers; freeze in plastic container or on cookie sheet and put into another container after frozen.
Keeps in freezer for 2 or 3 months.

title: pork tenderloin periscope(serves 6 to 8; oven temperature 450~ to 500~)
directions: Cut the tenderloin in about 4-inch sections so they are all about even.
Roll in black peppercorns.
Roll in melted butter, then roll in fresh bread crumbs mixed with thyme and parsley.
(Let rest to dry a bit.)

Dribble a little butter over each tenderloin and roast in 500° Fahrenheit oven for approximately 10 minutes or until it firms up and becomes crispy on outside (meat becomes firm to touch as it cooks).
The end product should be crispy on the outside but inside it's still faintly pink, yes it's cooked). Slice meat and arrange on plates.
(Sprinkle with salt, optional.)

title: pineapple cranberry mousse
directions: Drain 20 ounce can pineapple; reserve 1 cup juice.
Heat reserved juice to boiling; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
In food processor or blender, chop cranberries and sliced, unpeeled orange with sugar to make a relish.
Combine relish and pineapple with gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Garnish with 8 ounce can of pineapple and mint if desired.
Serves 10.
Chill time:
4 hours.

title: graham cracker delight icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread over Graham Cracker Delight Cake.

title: buttered rice
directions: Wash rice; combine all ingredients in 1-quart baking dish. Cover and cook 50 minutes.
It's always nice and fluffy.

title: evelyn moore's cheese loaf
directions: Grind all together.
Use enough mayonnaise to hold together, then mold and chill.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box. Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 300-325° until the layers test done. Cool.

title: cheesy potato chips
directions: Spread potato chips on a baking pan.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes, until hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in a small amount of the milk.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour into an ungreased, shallow, 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted at side comes out clean.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Saute chicken in oil until browned and cooked thoroughly.
Set aside; discard oil.
Toast sesame seed and almonds in pan in oven for approximately 10 minutes at 300°.
Set aside.
Toss together lettuce, onions and chicken.
Sprinkle almonds and sesame seed on top.
Just before serving, add noodles and pour dressing over the top.

title: "working for peanuts" pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping; spoon into crust and sprinkle with peanuts. Chill 8 hours.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: grandma novak pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening together.
Add water.
Mix all together and roll out.
Makes 1 double pie crust or 2 singles.

title: 5 bean baked beans
directions: *Should be as close to 16 ounce cans as possible.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie crust prepared by directions. Top with other pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Onions are optional.

title: italian stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove and chop mushroom stems.
Saute stems, onions and garlic in skillet in 2 tablespoons oil.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and oregano.
Add to skillet.

title: marinated pears
directions: Drain pears reserving 1 cup of the syrup.
Combine syrup, cinnamon stick, allspice and peppercorns.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over pears.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Mix browned bacon and onion to cooked rice and stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts.
Do not boil. Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Boil a fryer.
Debone chicken and return to pot.
Add onion, mixed vegetables and potatoes.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add tomato sauce.
Season to taste and heat thoroughly.

title: wedding punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar, then other ingredients.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and water gradually.
Pour over fried bacon and cook (stirring constantly until thick).
Use on iceberg lettuce, endive, dandelion or cabbage for hot slaw, etc.

title: potato soup
directions: Chop potatoes fine.
Boil on high in water 1 to 2 inches above top of potatoes.
When potatoes are done, add margarine.
Mix cornmeal mix with milk and add to potatoes.
Lower heat and cook on low, stirring constantly, until thick.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve piping hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as per directions; drain.
Mix mushroom soup into vegetables.
Place in casserole and cover top with onion rings; bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: huntington bay dip
directions: Saute bread crumbs, garlic powder, onion, salt and oregano in oil until golden brown.
Mix bread crumb mixture with clams and juice.
Add chopped parsley and grated cheese.
Pour into a shallow casserole dish or several small, shallow pans.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until dark brown.
Serve with crackers. If preparing ahead of time, clambake can be frozen before cooking.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed, until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: apricot jalapeno jelly
directions: Drain and
rinse
jalapeno
peppers.
Remove
stems and seeds. Combine pepper strips, vinegar and jalapeno peppers in blender. Process
until
small
chunks.
Combine with apricot and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and skim foam.	Cool 2 minutes.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Pound chicken breast flat.
Melt margarine.
Add mushrooms, olives and almonds.
Saute until almonds are golden brown.
Cut cream cheese into quarters.
Place one piece of cream cheese on each half breast.
Place 1/4 of the sauteed mixture on each breast half over cream cheese.
Roll chicken into balls.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat oil.
Add chicken rolls and brown on all sides.
Place each chicken roll on a 12 x 12-inch piece of foil. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bring points together but do not seal tightly.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 45 minutes or until done.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Mix well with apples.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter and add vanilla.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove all seeds and membranes.
Wash inside and out. Cook peppers in boiling salt water for 5 minutes; drain.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion until onion is tender.
Drain off fat. Stir in salt, garlic salt, rice and 1 cup of tomato sauce.
Lightly stuff each pepper with 1/2 cup meat mixture.
Stand peppers upright in ungreased baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: crunch pineapple cranberry mold
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling; pour over gelatin.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 10-inch ring mold and chill until firm. Unmold and garnish with pineapple slices and salad greens as desired.
Serves 10.
Can be frozen.

title: old time layered garden casserole(1930 depression)
directions: Layer ingredients in large casserole dish.
Season lightly between each layer.
Bake 2 hours in slow oven until done.
Cover for first 1/2 hour.

title: chicken broccoli rice skillet
directions: In skillet heat butter, cook carrots and green onions until tender.
Push to one side; add chicken.
Cook until browned on all sides.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover, simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork before serving.

title: rum balls(36 to 42 balls)
directions: Mix well vanilla wafer crumbs, cocoa, 1 cup confectioners sugar and pecans.
Add corn syrup and rum; mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in remaining confectioners sugar.
Put in tightly covered tin box or other metal container for at least 12 hours before serving.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Heat tuna, soup, cream cheese and onion until cheese is melted. Set aside.
Sprinkle gelatine over hot water and stir to dissolve. Add to tuna mixture.
Add celery.
Mix well and pour into mold. Chill thoroughly.
Unmold on bed of lettuce.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Crab, salmon or shrimp may be used in place of tuna.

title: west haven cake
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together then set aside. Mix the
last
five
ingredients
together in a separate bowl. Combine both mixtures.
Pour batter
into
cake pan.
Top with the remaining one-half pack of
chocolate
chips; bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: microwave deluxe scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs in bowl with fork.
Add cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and bacon.
Blend well.
Set aside.
Place margarine in 1-quart casserole dish.
Heat on full power 30 to 45 seconds, until melted.
Coat evenly.
Pour eggs into casserole dish.
Cook on full power 3 1/2 to 5 minutes until eggs are set, but still moist.
Stir a couple of times while cooking.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Put browned beef and onion in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Cover with chili beans (undrained).
Cover with Spanish rice.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: duck gumbo
directions: Boil 2 or 3 ducks, covered with water, salt and bay leaves until ducks are tender (save stock).
Fry bacon (save drippings). Add flour to drippings, enough to consume liquid.
Heat and stir until brown.
Add onions, celery and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add to duck juice with tomatoes, okra, sausage, duck and a dash of thyme, basil and oregano (optional), if desired.
Add shrimp last 8 minutes.
Cook approximately 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook crumbled sausage and drain.
Line greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish with crescent rolls.
Add sausage and cover with grated cheese.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes until set.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with the 1/4 cup cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: cheese dip
directions: Saute onion in butter, then add cheese, green chilies and soup.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: frank e.'s buffalo wings
directions: Rinse wings.
Divide at joints; discard tips.
Pat dry.
Fry in deep fat at 400° for about 12 minutes or until wings float. Drain on paper towels.

title: spears of asparagus en casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease casserole. Combine all ingredients, reserving part of cheese. Top with reserved cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly. Yield: 8 servings.

title: frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick and cool.
Blend shortening, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Add flour and milk and beat until thick and creamy.
Good frosting for carrot cake.

title: night before casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding pepper to taste.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix together and place in container.
Place in refrigerator. Drink 2 ounces a day.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture.
Fold in nuts and zucchini.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in 2 greased loaf pans.
If using 6 small pans, bake for 45 minutes.

title: noreen's fruitcake
directions: Use a 9-inch tube pan.
Line with wax paper; butter lining. Sift flour and baking soda together; set aside.
In large bowl, mix together all other ingredients.
Fold in flour mixture; put in pan.
Cook for 2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn out of pan; remove paper.
Cool.

title: layered salad
directions: Start with spinach and layer first four ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to seal, approximately 1/2 to 3/4 cup.
Add Swiss cheese, bacon and eggs.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt, brown sugar and nutmeg together.
Mix together milk, egg and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to mix.
Fill greased baking pan. Bake at 425°
about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Let bread set out, opened overnight.
Tear bread into cubes; mix sugar and cinnamon in bread.
Melt butter, add milk, eggs, raisins, vanilla and brown sugar.
Pour over bread and mix well. Add pie filling and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown on top and set in middle.
Top each serving with caramel topping and whipped cream.
Serve warm. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: christmas snow punch
directions: In a punch bowl combine all ingredients.
Stir until well blended.

title: confetti pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, combine oil, lemon juice, green onions and seasonings.
Add hot pasta.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; chill.

title: fish italiano
directions: Pour butter into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange onion evenly on bottom of dish.
Place fish filets in a single layer atop the onion.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and salt.
Spread evenly on top of fish.
Sprinkle, to taste, with oregano and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: turkey amandine
directions: Combine turkey, soup, peas, chestnuts, mushrooms, celery, salt, pepper and sour cream.
Cook over medium heat until hot. Pour into 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
Unroll rolls into 2 long rectangles.
Place over turkey mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and almonds.
Bake 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat, simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend all of mixture (1/3 at a time) in electric blender for 20 seconds. Repeat until all ingredients are blended.
Pour back into Dutch oven.
Stir in milk and simmer 20 minutes.

title: beef birds
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Soften butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add flavorings.
Gradually add flour.
(I use star press and make into small circles.)
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes until lightly browned.
Watch carefully.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Add onion and crumbled bacon.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar. Pour over vegetables.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Slice 6 strawberries and reserve.
Puree remaining berries in processor or blender.
Strain into 4-quart saucepan.
Add orange juice.
In small bowl, mix tapioca with 4 tablespoons pureed berry mixture.
Add to saucepan with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Heat, stirring constantly, until comes to a boil. Cook 1 minute at medium heat or until thick. Remove from heat.
Pour into large bowl. Add sugar, lemon peel and juice and buttermilk. Blend well. Fold in sliced berries. Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Serve with lemon garnish. Can be prepared 3 days ahead.
Serves 4.

title: reception punch
directions: In 6-quart nonmetal container, combine all ingredients except carbonated beverage.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Just before serving, combine juice mixture and carbonated in a large punch bowl.
Serve over ice or float ice ring in punch bowl.
Makes 40 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Line cup cake pan with paper cups (cup cake cups).
Put 1 vanilla wafer
in
each
cup.
Beat
together
cream cheese, eggs, sugar and
vanilla until smooth.
Spoon into cups on top of wafers.
Bake at
for
minutes.
Cool and place a spoonful of pie filling on each cheese cake.
Serve cold.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add pizza sauce.
Pour into 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle cheese over hamburger and pizza sauce.
Mix eggs, milk, flour, oil and salt.
Pour over cheese and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana yogurt salad
directions: Peel and split bananas; place in serving dishes.
Spoon one cup of yogurt into each banana.
Sprinkle with nuts; surround with orange sections and shredded lettuce.

title: marinated noodles
directions: Mix and marinate overnight.
Makes 1 gallon ice cream pail.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 mix in a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. While cake is baking, melt caramels and cream over medium heat. Pour over baked layer of cake followed by chocolate chips then pecans, if desired.
Pour remaining cake mix over top and bake again about 25 minutes.

title: cauliflower broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in water until tender.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together and pour over vegetables in dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all.
Pour it into pie crust.

title: pound cake to die for
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 1 tube or 2 loaf pans. Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Alternate flour-baking powder with milk.
Add vanilla and lemon. Pour into pans and bake approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes for tube pan or 1 hour for loaf pan.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Melt butter and chips.
Stir in marshmallows and milk.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread 1/2 jar of peanuts on the bottom of the pan.
Pour marshmallow mixture on the peanuts; spread and press.
Put the remainder of the peanuts on top and press them in. Cool them in the refrigerator and cut into bars.

title: cheese sticks
directions: First, toast your bread and then put cheese on your bread. Then put it in the microwave for 21 seconds.
Take it out and then cut it in long strips.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add next three.
Sprinkle raisins on top and press down into mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes until golden brown.
Use 10-inch pan.

title: tin can ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients in a 1-pound coffee can with a tight-fitting plastic lid.
Place lid on can and put can in a large #10 can, also with a plastic lid.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir to blend. Cover and chill. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Roll half of pastry on lightly floured surface.
Place in a 9-inch pie pan.
Set aside.
Combine apple juice and cornstarch in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Add oleo, cinnamon and nutmeg, mixing well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon mixture in pie pan.
Roll remaining crust.
Put on top of apples.
Fold edges under and flute.
Cut slits on top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 30 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Mix all ingredients and put into greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cook until brown.
Combine and add next 6 ingredients; simmer for 1 hour.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, sauce and sprinkle Parmesan on top (3 layers) in buttered pan.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook and cube potatoes.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion in butter until golden.
Combine flour, salt, sugar and celery seed.
Add to onion and cook until bubbly. Combine water and vinegar.
Stir into onion mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Add cooked potatoes and bacon and stir until well mixed. Heat through.
Serves 4.

title: wednesday frosty
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender on high speed until smooth (milkshake consistency).
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter french toast
directions: Blend peanut butter, honey and salt. Place about 2 1/2 tablespoons of peanut butter-honey mixture between 2 slices of bread to make a sandwich. Combine eggs and the milk. Soak sandwiches in egg mixture. Melt butter or margarine in a baking pan or frypan. Bake sandwiches at 400° (hot oven) about 40 minutes. Turn sandwiches to brown both sides. Or cook slowly in frypan on top of range. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until clear.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain well.
Mix with broccoli, soup and cheese.
Add to celery and onions.
Stir in rice and seasonings. Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be mixed ahead and frozen.

title: smoked pork and vegetable soup
directions: Cook smoked pork chops and take meat off bones. Cook meat and navy beans in broth until beans are just about tender. Add water as needed. Add the other vegetables and seasonings. Put in a big pot or crock-pot. Cook all day. It tastes better served the next day.

title: monterey jack salsa
directions: Blend all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and pastry
directions: Cover chicken with water about 1 inch over.
Cook covered until tender.
Remove and cool.
Debone chicken.
Add pastry to boiling liquid.
Cook until tender (skim off excess fat).
Add deboned chicken.
Serve piping hot.

title: judy's spaghetti
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add to browned meat.
Place all ingredients together and add tomatoes.
Cook spaghetti to package directions.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix dressing mix and oil in a large bowl.
Dump crackers in mix and stir to coat thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: beef-rice creole
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Sprinkle beef with flour and salt.
Stir in green pepper, onion, parsley, pepper, pepper sauce, garlic, bay leaf and thyme. Cook over low heat until onion is tender.
Stir water and tomatoes (with liquid) into beef, break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice, remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Crush ritz crackers.
Melt butter in 9 x 13 glass dish in microwave.
Spread crackers on top of melted butter.
Bake 350 - 10 minutes.

title: pita pockets
directions: Fry pita bread in a very little bit of oil until brown.
Open pita and put sauce and cheese inside.
Microwave to melt cheese.

title: meatballs in barbecue sauce
directions: Saute chopped onions in the oil.
Mix all ingredients together and shape into balls.
Place into a greased 9 x 12-inch dish and cover with the following sauce.

title: cucumber crunch
directions: Combine cucumbers, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
Allow to stand 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add onion and sour cream.
Stir until well blended.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: jiffy rice casserole
directions: Combine onion and rice and cook as package directs.
Blend in sour cream and Jiffy Jack.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: "philly" rainbow tart
directions: Combine 1/2 package cream cheese and margarine.
Mix well. Add flour and salt; mix well.
Form into ball and chill.
On lightly floured surface, roll to 14-inch circle.
Place in 12-inch tart or pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Combine remaining cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream and spoon into cooled crust. Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Brush with combined preserves and water.
Chill.
Makes 10 servings.

title: spicy chili
directions: Need 8 quart pot.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Pour off grease.
To the browned beef and onion add chili mix, diced tomatoes and chili peppers, crushed tomatoes and water in the 8 quart pot and simmer a couple of hours.
Add more chili powder or water as needed.
I usely add one (1) tablespoon chili powder extra.
Add chili hot beans and simmer until beans are warm.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add flavoring; add eggs one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking soda and cocoa.
Mix well into butter, sugar and egg mixture. Fold in sour cream.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for about 1 hour and 15 or 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.
Can be made in small or large loaf pans.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Grate cheese.
In a small bowl, beat the egg.
Then add the milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat with a fork until there are no lumps of flour.

title: hot spiced fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits, reserving 3/4 cup syrup.
Arrange fruit in 2-quart casserole.
Pour lemon juice over top.
Combine fruit syrup, sugar and spices.
Pour over fruits.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
If desired, whipped topping may be used.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: seafood nachos
directions: In a bowl, grate together sea legs, shrimp and crab.
On a large serving plate, spread chips.
Sprinkle seafood mixture over chips, then cheese over seafood.
Microwave on High 30 to 45 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream, salsa or hot sauce.

title: dave gunter's cole slaw or potato salad dressing
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together, then add 1/2 tablespoon celery seed, salt seasoning and garlic to taste.

title: jellied beet and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain beets and pineapple (reserve all juice).
Add enough water to the juice to measure
2 1/2 cups liquid.
Pour this liquid into dissolved gelatin.
Add vinegar and salt to taste.
Chill until partially set, then stir in beets and pineapple.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Soften cream cheese
and then gradually add lemon pie filling mixed according to directions on box.
Pour into pie crust. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Chill 2 hours.

title: candy apple delight
directions: Combine whipped topping and drained pineapple in bowl.
Peel and slice apples.
Cut Snickers into small cubes.
Chop peanuts. Fold in apples, candy and peanuts.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Stir together all ingredients using hands or spoon. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place in a lightly greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown. Remove immediately from pan and serve warm with sauce for dipping.

title: rolos cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except Rolos.
May need to chill.
Form a ball around each Rolo.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry in oil.

title: ginger and peach chicken
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender and no longer pink; turn to brown evenly.
Remove from skillet; keep warm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish or buttered pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 60 minutes, stirring occasionally until done.

title: pasta sauce raphael
directions: Drain the artichoke hearts, reserving the marinade.
Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan.
Add the onions, garlic, basil, black pepper, salt, red pepper flakes and reserved artichoke marinade.
Saute over medium to low heat until the onion and garlic are soft and translucent, 10 minutes.
Add the tomatoes and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add the artichoke hearts, Parmesan and parsley. Stir gently and simmer another 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Heat pie filling in a chafing dish or in frypan.
Warm brandy; spoon over warm cherries.
Do not stir.
Light surface with match. Spoon over ice cream while still flaming.
Makes 2 2/3 cups of sauce.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well & chill.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender.
Pour into unbaked, deep-dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins and cool.
Peel potatoes and grate coarsely.
In pan over low heat, melt butter, onion and cheese. Add sour cream and seasoning.
Mix well.
Add potatoes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: supreme chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken covered in water and seasoned with seasoning salt and pepper until tender.
Cool chicken in stock.
Remove chicken from bones.
Cut if necessary.
Using stock, cook cut celery, cut green peppers, chopped onions and mushrooms.
Add chopped pimento and sliced olives and enough flour to thicken slightly.
Add almonds and cut-up chicken.
Cook spaghetti in stock if enough remains or in water with chicken cubes until tender.
Taste stock for seasoning.
In a casserole dish layer chicken mixture, cheese, spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Make layers thin so seasoning will go through.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend in food processor. Cook in large pot until mixture becomes the right consistency for relish and pour into hot sterile jars. Wonderful on meats.

title: mrs. c. l. elliott's old fashioned ice cream custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and flour.
Heat milk, add to egg mixture.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Cool.
Add flavorings.
Strain to remove lumps.

title: donna's italian sausage and peppers hors d'oeuvre
directions: Cut sausage with scissors into 1 1/2 to 2-inch
pieces in olive oil.
Fry over low heat stirring occasionally.
Salt and add a little pepper, 1 at a time.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Put all in crock-pot.
Serve with toothpicks and a side dish of warm spaghetti sauce as a dip.

title: family french dressing
directions: In jar, combine ketchup, salad oil, vinegar, confectioners sugar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and shake.
Chill to blend flavors.
Remove garlic.
Shake again before serving.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: spareribs with apples
directions: About 3 hours before serving, preheat oven to 400°.
In large shallow roasting pan, place ribs, meaty side up.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bake 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: ground beef hot dish
directions: Brown beef, celery and onion.
Add soup, mushrooms, rice, soy sauce and water.
Mix and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: small pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add milk alternately with flour and baking powder.
Beat well.
Blend in extract.
Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: anniversary cake
directions: Combine all.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325° in a Bundt pan.

title: kraut salad
directions: Wash and drain kraut; mix in remaining ingredients.
Let stand to blend taste.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in order.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Pour the 3 cans of soup into a small bowl.
Add 1 can of water and mix well.
Pour this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Bake in slow oven at 350° for approximately 1 or 1 1/2 hours.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Pour melted butter over nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and slowly add sugar.
Mix into nuts.
Spread on cookie sheet but not to edges.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Every 10 minutes, turn nuts with a spatula.
Remove nuts from oven if golden brown before 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and egg yolks; beat well.
Add flour with sour cream alternately.
Fold in beaten egg whites and all flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: crab stuffed flounder
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in small saucepan.
Blend in flour and sour cream.
Stir until thick.
Add wine.
Add 1/2 cup of this sauce with bread crumbs and crab meat.
Spread on fillets, roll up.
Place seam side down.
Sprinkle with cracker meal. Garnish with dill.
Dot pan with margarine.
Cook in oven at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.
Pour remaining sauce over rolls.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; let stand for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Divide dough into two coffee cans. Replace plastic lids.
Grease these!
After about 2 hours, when lids lift off, remove lids and bake bread 45 minutes at 350°. Loaves can be twisted out of the cans easily after a few minutes. Cool on rack in upright position.
Crust will be brown.
